title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Combine tomato juice, celery, and onion.
Stir often.
Heat gently for 30 minutes.
Add lemon juice, sugar, salt, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes. This can be served hot or chilled.
Makes 5 pints.

title: copper pennies or glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; cool and slice.
Layer carrots, pepper and onion.
Cook salad oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce, mustard and sugar until blended.
Pour sauce over carrot mixture.
Better if allowed to marinate for 24 hours. Refrigerate.

title: italian cracker snacks
directions: Preheat oven 250°. Place crackers in a large shallow baking pan. In a small bowl, combine butter, salad dressing mix, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Pour butter mixture over crackers; stir well. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Pour onto waxed paper to cool. Store in airtight container. Yields approximately 4 cups snack mix.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) or cookie sheet.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured surface.
Knead 20 times.
Pat dough on bottom and sides of pan with floured hands.
Cook and stir beef, onion, salt and garlic until the beef is brown; drain.
Mix the tomato sauce and Italian seasoning.
Spread evenly over dough.
Spoon beef mixture evenly over sauce.
Top with mushrooms, green peppers and cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: paula's hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box; let cool. Drain pineapple. Blend cream cheese and vanilla pudding with a little milk to soften. Add the rest of the milk. Fold in pineapple. Spread mixture on top of cake. Put sliced strawberries on top of mixture. Spread on Cool Whip. Enjoy!

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: In saucepan, cover carrot slices with water and cook until tender.
Drain carrots, reserving liquid.
Cool.
In saucepan, combine vinegar, sugar, onion, parsley, pickling spice and 1/2 of the reserved carrot liquid.
Simmer to blend flavors, then add carrots.
Cool, covered, then refrigerate at least 8 hours to marinate.
Can be reheated in liquid or serve cold.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and cook on low for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: date cheese ball
directions: Form into a ball and cover with toasted slivered almonds. Serve with crackers.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples and cut in halves, remove the core.
Wrap each half of apple in biscuit by stretching it over the apple half. Place in baking dish.
In a boiler, heat water, margarine, sugar and cinnamon until margarine is melted.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 325° to 400° for 45 minutes, basting with juice every 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients
in a large mixing bowl and mix well. Bake in a greased
and
floured
tube or Bundt pan in a 350° oven, about 40
minutes,	or you can bake in two (9-inch) layer pans for 25 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Scald milk.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks, gradually adding sugar and salt.
Add scalded milk.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes. Cool completely.
When ready to churn, beat egg whites stiff. Fold into milk.
Add evaporated milk (add peaches, if desired). Freeze until hard, then it is ready to eat.

title: holiday dip
directions: Combine all with mixer.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers, toast points and chips.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: miniature date fruitcakes
directions: In mixing bowl, prepare mix per instructions on package.
Add candied fruit, pecans and raisins.
Mix.
Spoon into 24 paper-lined cups (muffin small).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Glaze with warm corn syrup and garnish with candied cherries.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Will also need a well greased 10-inch tube pan.

title: one-pan chicken pasta meal
directions: Saute chicken, garlic and onions in small amount of vegetable oil until onions are clear.
Add pasta and veggies.
Add approximately 3 cups of hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until pasta is done.
Salt to taste.

title: irish creme liqueur
directions: Put all the ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth. Store tightly covered, up to one month in refrigerator.

title: caviar pie
directions: Prepare an 8-inch spring-form pan by covering bottom with aluminum foil and lining sides with plastic wrap.
Spread 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with onions.
Combine eggs and mayonnaise and spread gently over onions.
Combine 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese with sour cream. Spread gently over egg mixture.
Cover with plastic and chill overnight.
To serve, release spring-form and place pie on the foil covered spring-form bottom onto serving dish.
Just before serving, spread black caviar over cream cheese/sour cream layer. Serve with crackers.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Toss ingredients together and just prior to serving add 1 can shoestring potatoes.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat eggs and stir in sugar and oil.
Mix dry ingredients except soda.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Stir in prunes and nuts.
Bake in greased pan for 55 to 60 minutes or until tests done.
Remove from pan and frost.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix chicken, soup and sour cream.
Place in rectangular baking dish.
Top with prepared dressing.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: luscious guava gelatin
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water to soften.
Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water.
Add guava concentrate, sugar and softened gelatin.
Stir in and pour into container.
Chill until firm.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine sugar and pineapple. Boil 3 minutes. Add lemon jello and set off eye of stove. Add cream cheese. Cool and add rest of ingredients. If you double this recipe, it will make a 9 x 13 pan; otherwise, 6 x 9 or 8 x 8.

title: little devils
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in heavy pan.
Add butter flavoring and nuts.
Stir to cool and remove from heat.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Do not beat! Add chocolate mixture and again mix carefully but do not beat. Put into 18 paper cups and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Add water and ice.
Do not put in metal container.
Makes 5 gallons.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet-sour dressing
directions: Chop up onion.
Put in blender and liquify it.
Add all the other ingredients and blend until sugar and salt are completely dissolved.
Add 1 pint of salad oil, 1 cup at a time.
Blend well.

title: dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and add 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together for 5 minutes using mixer the remaining ingredients.
Pour over cake mixture in pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine and refrigerate for 24 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: super easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix sugar, peanut butter, egg and vanilla in a bowl with spoon. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake
at 300° for 15 to 18 minutes or until light.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
(Be careful, cookies have a tendency to burn on the bottom.
Watch carefully.)
Yields approximately 2 dozen cookies.

title: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and food coloring.
Combine cake flour and cocoa. Dissolve soda in vinegar; add to buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Pour yeast and sugar into warm water.
Let stand until bubbles up.
Mix yeast mixture in with flour, salt and olive oil.
Knead dough.
After kneading, form into ball.
Place in bowl and let rise.
Should take 45 minutes.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Serve on Ritz crackers and top with cocktail sauce.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Add Eagle Brand and vanilla.
Stir in Cool Whip.
In large dish layer 1/2 box cookies, sliced bananas and pudding.
Top with rest of cookies.
Make one day ahead.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs, milk, butter and vanilla.
Mix well with mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fried okra
directions: Cut large okra in 1-inch or more slices.
Sprinkle with meal. Dip in egg and meal again (roll or shake in bag).
Fry in shortening.
Drain on paper towels.

title: rice crispy cookies
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar on medium heat just until boiling. Cool.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Rice Krispies. Press into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips together and frost cookies with this mixture.

title: wet crust shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and shortening.
Reserve 3/4 cup mixture
for topping.
To remainder add other filling ingredients. Beat well.
Pour into pie
shell.
Add reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: whole wheat loaves
directions: Sprinkle yeast on 1 1/2 cups lukewarm water; stir to dissolve. Add flour, sugar and salt.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Cover and let rise in warm place until light and bubbly.
Combine 1/2 cup hot water, brown sugar and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add brown sugar mixture to yeast; mix well.
Add enough whole wheat flour to make a soft dough that leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth and satiny.
Place dough in lightly greased bowl; turn over to greased top.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Divide dough in half.
Shape into balls.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape each half into a loaf.
Place in two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until loaves sound hollow when tapped. Remove from pans.
Brush tops with melted butter.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal, flour and onions.
Add the egg and oil.
Stir in milk.
Mix until all ingredients are damp.
Drop by tablespoon into hot cooking oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: 5 bean soup(very hearty)
directions: Place all beans (except limas) in bowl and cover with water. Soak overnight.
Soak limas separately.
Cover ham hock and sausage with water and boil.
Add carrot, celery and parsley. Simmer 1 hour, but remove sausage after 15 minutes. Set aside. Saute onion in olive oil. Add garlic and set aside. Drain and remove grease for hock water.
Discard veggies.
Remove meat from hock and chop coarsely.
Dispose of skin and bone.
Drain mixed beans and put in a large pot.
Measure degreased water and add water to make 4 cups.
Pour over beans.
Boil.
Add onion-garlic mixture.
Simmer; add spices.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add tomatoes, beef stock and lima beans.
Simmer another 30 minutes. Cut sausage into 1/4-inch rings.
Add to soup with ham and vinegar. Simmer 10 minutes more. Serve!
Very good.
Hot.
Good Tex-Mex!

title: hamburger-mashed potato casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown the hamburger, salt, pepper, onion, sugar and green pepper. Add the drained beans and tomatoes and stir gently. Transfer to a casserole dish. Pipe outer edge with mashed potatoes. Sprinkle grated cheese over potatoes.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise into halves; remove seeds.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix cucumbers, soup, water chestnuts and milk; heat to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until cucumbers are tender (about 6 minutes).
Stir in dill weed and pimiento.

title: chicken spaghetti with cheese
directions: Cook the chicken in boiling salted water until tender enough to fall off the bones. Remove meat from bones and dice.
Measure stock and add water to make 1 quart. Add the celery, onions, peppers and spaghetti to pan. Cook until pasta is tender. Fold in the chicken, pimiento and mushrooms.
Cook until just warm.
Stir in the cheese.
Pour into baking dish and chill 24 hours.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 10 servings. Garnish each serving with sliced green olives and serve.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Wash rice in hot water until all starch is removed. Saute onions in margarine for 5 minutes. Pour over rice and stir until all grains of rice are covered with margarine. Mix chicken base and white pepper with hot water until dissolved. Stir into rice. Place in suitable pan and cover. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Mix green and red diced pepper into cooked rice.

title: quick chocolate frosting
directions: Put margarine, cocoa and milk in pot and bring to a boil. Pour over xxxx sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Spread on cake.

title: swiss cheese lasagne
directions: In a large skillet, cook the beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Add Prego sauce, bring to boil. Lower temperature to low and simmer for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, cook lasagne noodles according to package directions; drain. In a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish, spread some of the meat sauce in bottom of pan. Layer noodles, swiss cheese slices, cottage cheese and some mozzarella. Cover with meat sauce; then repeat layers. Reserve a portion of mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover, add mozzarella to top and bake for 15 minutes uncovered. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. Yields 12 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and enjoy.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: kitchen spice potpourri
directions: Mix well.
Must be kept in an airtight glass jar.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil and serve hot.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Heat bacon drippings; add a little flour at a time until it is a golden brown.
Pour in tomatoes.
Let thicken.
Use salt and pepper to taste.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook in 1-quart saucepan.
Mix sugar and flour together in a saucepan.
Add water and vinegar.
Cook on medium heat until thick, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, butter or margarine and diced beets.
Cook until beets are heated through.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in bottom of 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish.
Add sugar and water.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Cut in fat and add milk.
Mix lightly and spread dough over peaches.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan snowballs
directions: Cream margarine, vanilla, sugar, salt, flour and pecans. Shape in 1-inch balls, place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix sugar, coconut, milk, butter and nuts. Make into balls and chill.
Melt chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini as directed.
Rinse and cool.
Toss all ingredients in creamy Italian salad dressing and serve.

title: angelloni lemon cookies
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients thoroughly.
Dough will be sticky. Let dough set for about 1/2 hour.
Place on greased cookie sheet in small balls.
(Be sure there are no cracks in the balls).
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.
Do not overcook; will be very light. When completely cooled, frost.

title: sweet and sour pork(serves 12)
directions: Place pork, water, soy sauce and garlic in pot; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer about 50 minutes, until pork is tender. Discard garlic.
Drain broth and reserve.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and spices. Dissolve soda in water; add to mixture.
Add flour, jam, raisins, coconut and vanilla; beat well.
Bake in 2 large pans for 30 to 40 minutes in a 325° oven, or until done.

title: copper penny relish
directions: Wash and scrape carrots.
Cut into round slices, cover with salt water and boil just until tender (firm not soft).
Drain and cool the carrots.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt stick of butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 300°.
Spread 1 cup graham cracker crumbs in pan.
Put the other 4 ingredients in one layer at a time.
Put Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti. Dissolve bouillon cube in water. add soup, celery, salt and pepper. Add spaghetti. Stir in cubed chicken and half of cheese. Pour in a greased pan. Top with remaining cheeses. Bake 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: 36 lady prune cake
directions: Beat prunes and water until prunes are chopped.
Blend with remaining ingredients.
(I use large spoon instead of mixer.) Bake in greased and floured 12-cup tube pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Spread 1/2 of crumbs in pan or dish.
Add sugar mixture.
Add layer of whipped cream combined with nuts.
Top with remaining wafer crumbs.
Chill at least 12 hours.

title: crabmeat canape
directions: Mix and spread on muffin halves. Cut each half into quarters. Freeze at least 10 minutes, then broil until bubbly and brown. Can freeze for later use if desired.

title: ham and succotash chowder
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add thyme, celery seed, broth, beans, corn and ham.
Boil on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add potato flakes, whisking in until thick and smooth, then stir in milk and bring to desired temperature.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix together and sift the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Then add corn oil, buttermilk and dry yeast dissolved in warm water.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator in a tightly closed container.
Dip out as needed. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes on a greased cookie sheet. Mixture should be stored at least 1 day before using.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Press crescent rolls into pie crust for 9-inch pan.
Brown hamburger, onion, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add tomato paste and pour into pie shell.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pinoy chicken adobo
directions: Clean chicken thoroughly with lemon or salt.
Rinse well. Place all the ingredients into a casserole dish.
Mix and marinate for at least 1 hour.
Taste.
Simmer, but do not mix for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix well so the juices are evenly distributed.
Lower the fire and cook for another 10 minutes. Serve when ready.

title: liv's candy bar cookies
directions: Chop Snickers bar into small pieces. Break or chop Hershey bar. Mix brownie mix with other ingredients except candy and nuts. Fold in candy and nuts. Place on greased cookie sheets. Bake in preheated 375° oven 7 to 9 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: chow mein noodle cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch morsels over a double boiler.
In a mixing bowl, put noodles and marshmallows.
Add your melted mixture over noodles and marshmallows, then mix.
Then drop by spoonful on a piece of foil.
Let cool.
No cooking or baking. Makes lots.

title: strawberry jam
directions: In a large kettle, mix together strawberries, sugar and corn syrup.
Quickly bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook rapidly, 30 to 40 minutes, or until jam sheets from a metal spoon and becomes clear in color.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking and skim with a metal spoon as foam rises to the surface.
Remove from heat; cool 5 minutes, stirring gently.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Seal according to jar manufacturers directions.

title: hoppin' good salad
directions: In a bowl, beat cream cheese and gelatin powder.
Stir in water until gelatin is dissolved.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until thickened, stirring frequently.
Set aside 10 to 12 oranges for garnish.
Fold Cool Whip, 3/4 cup marshmallows and remaining oranges into gelatin mixture.
Transfer to a 2 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Sprinkle with remaining marshmallows.
Chill until firm. Garnish with reserved oranges.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon drop cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, Cool Whip and egg by hand. Chill. Roll into balls, then drop into powdered sugar. Bake at 325° about 12 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: gulliver's creamed corn
directions: Combine ingredients (except butter, flour and cheese) in a 3-quart pan and bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes. Melt butter in small pan and blend in flour. Add to corn. Mix well and remove from heat.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Drain eggplant from juice.
Mix eggplant, egg and onion until sticky.
Stir flour and baking powder into milk; stir in eggplant mixture.
Form into patties or drop with spoon into hot Crisco. Fry until golden brown, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put the first 7 ingredients (add in order) all together in a bowl and mix well with a whisk.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: linda's tarbox chicken
directions: Fry chicken until brown.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: barbecue sauce and meat
directions: Cook until brown sugar dissolves (about 20 minutes in electric skillet).
Place chicken or pork in sauce until done.

title: wild plum muffins
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil, continue beating well.
Add flour and plums.
Add allspice and nuts.
Mix well.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: coleslaw
directions: Grate and mix together first three ingredients.
Mix rest of ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil and pour over slaw. Refrigerate before serving.

title: corned beef balls in celery sauce
directions: Flake corned beef with fork.
Add bread, onion, egg and potato.
Mix and shape into 12 balls.
Brown on all sides in hot margarine in frying pan.
Place in casserole dish.
Add hot water to celery soup and mix.
Pour over balls.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.
(Can be prepared day before, adding soup when ready to cook.)
Serve over medium-wide noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk, coconut and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: yam and cranberry casserole
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, oats and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Toss 1 cup crumb mix with yams and cranberries.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with marshmallows and broil until brown.

title: lo-cal ambrosia
directions: Mix well; cover and refrigerate.

title: fluffy orange pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch pie plate, or use a ready made pie crust.
Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add juice concentrate and orange rind; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping; pour into crust. Freeze for 2 hours and enjoy.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Stir just before serving, mixing well.

title: dill pickles
directions: Heat
water, vinegar and salt to boiling.
Pack pickles in jar.
Add
large head dill, 1/4 teaspoon turmeric and 2 sections
garlic
per
jar.
Cold pack to boiling point.
Turn heat off and let stand 5 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and place 3 or 4 slices of bacon on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk, mashed bananas and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350°.

title: crunchy peanut butter pies
directions: In a large bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar and peanut butter, beating until well blended. Gradually stir in milk.
Fold whipped topping into cream cheese mixture; spoon into crust.
Garnish each pie with chopped peanuts.

title: yellow cake mandarin orange
directions: Beat together all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: venison roast
directions: Serve orange juice, cereal, warm rolls and hot coffee with scrambled eggs which have been garnished with broiled bacon, liver, tomato and eggplant.
Good.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form into ball.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut peeled potatoes into cubes.
Chop onion up finely.
Cook potatoes, onion and parsley flakes until almost done.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstrach to pot and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch to 1/2 cup water and add to potatoes; continue to simmer until thickened.
If thickness is not to desired level, continue to add cornstarch, a little at a time, until you reach desired thickness.

title: low cholesterol no bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, milk, margarine, sugar and vanilla together in pan. Bring to a boil; then add peanut butter.
Stir until melted. Remove from heat and immediately stir in oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper by the spoonful.
Makes 4 dozen.
One cookie equals 0 mg cholesterol.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Blend in flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in buttermilk and pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until set.
Cool on wire rack. Store in refrigerator.

title: raisin bars
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar; cut in 1/3 cup butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Press into bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine eggs and next 8 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake batter at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jennifer's divinity candy
directions: Combine frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in a small mixer bowl.
Beat on highest speed for about 5 to 6 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Transfer to a large mixing bowl on low speed; gradually blend in sugar.
Stir in nuts and then drop small amounts onto waxed paper.
Let dry for about three to four days before eating.
It helps to turn them over after one day.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop cranberries and oranges (with peel on) in food processor. Add pecans and sugar.
Make Jell-O according to package, using less water.
Add Jell-O to mixture and stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter. Pour this over corn flakes and coconut. Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and let set.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in food processor.
Can be frozen.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes (French fry style).
In a Corning Ware dish, layer potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and 2 or 3 tablespoons butter until all potatoes are used.
Cover; cook for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: senator's bean soup
directions: Cover
ham hock with water and cook.
Debone and cut up fine. Put
aside
and
save
broth.
Combine celery and tops, green onions
and tops, garlic and carrots.
Cover with water and simmer
until tender (not overdone).
Combine ham, broth, vegetables,
beans
and
potato
flakes and heat until hot and blended.

title: chicken with cashew nuts
directions: Dice chicken breasts.
Add the egg white and cornstarch. Season with salt, ajinomoto, soy sauce and sugar.
Blend very well. Set aside.
Fry cashew nuts in cooking oil until brown and crisp. Set aside.
Deep fat fry chicken breasts.
Drain out fat.
Disperse 1 tablespoon cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Add to chicken and continue cooking.
Top with crisp cashew nuts.
Serve.

title: stir and roll pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
In another bowl, mix oil and milk.
Mix oil and milk with flour and salt. Make into dough, divide in half and roll between two pieces of wax paper. Makes two crusts, either top and bottom crust or two bottoms.

title: banana split cake
directions: Take graham crackers and 1 stick butter. Melt butter and mix together.
Put in bottom of pan.
Beat 2 sticks of butter with 2 cups powdered sugar and 1 egg; beat 15 minutes at high speed.
Put in pinch of salt.
Pour cream mixture over crust.
Put layer of banana and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Put cherries and nuts on top.

title: sally's pumpkin bread
directions: Bake one hour 350°.
Test with toothpick.
This makes 3 loaf pans or 5 small loaf pans.
This will freeze well.

title: "no fail" pie crust
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Mix egg and water.
Combine both mixtures and form a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes.
Makes 5 (9-inch) pie shells.

title: no cook pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and fill 1/2 gallon jar with whole cucumbers. Do not cut or slice.
Add vinegar, salt, pickling spices and alum and finish filling jar with cold water.
Seal jar.
Let stand at least 2 months before opening.

title: never fail cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be very stiff.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 12 dozen. You can do anything with these cookies by adding something to them like nuts, coconut, chocolate chips, gumdrops, M&M's, etc.

title: caramel turtle brownies
directions: Combine cake mix with melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Press 1/2 of mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Melt caramels with remaining milk.
Pour in pan. Cover with reserved cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: easy salad
directions: Combine sour cream and pudding mix.
Add pineapple and coconut. Stir until blended.
Spoon into a loaf pan and freeze until firm, at least 3 hours.
Unmold by dipping pan in warm water.
Makes 3 cups or 6 servings.

title: bread or rolls
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast; mix in enough flour to make sponge (a good sponge is about like cake batter, only a little stiffer), then add and whip in good, the melted shortening.
Let rise, then add more flour as you knead into a good soft bread dough.
Let rise twice more and then mold into rolls and bake.

title: mona's pound cake
directions: Combine margarine and shortening.
Beat in the sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, while beating on low speed. Gradually blend flour, milk and flavorings.
Beat mixture at high speed for 15 minutes.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour or until done at 300°.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in skillet.
Drain.
Put hamburger back in skillet and add tomato sauce and the next 4 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 3/4 hour.
Mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, salt and oregano.
In oblong baking dish, layer 1/2 of the noodles, sauce and cheese mixture; repeat.
Reserve enough sauce for thin layer on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: one step supper rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl combine sour cream and egg.
Add pancake mix (measure by lightly spooning into cup and leveling off), blend until well moistened.
Drop by tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with poppy seeds or sesame seeds.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve warm.
(To reheat - wrap loosely in tin foil and heat at 350° for about 10 minutes.)

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together Snowdrift, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla; blend.
Stir
dry
ingredients
together
to
creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Mix
in oats, raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: hot hamwiches
directions: Butter bread on both sides.
Place 6 slices in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix ham and mustard and spread over bread slices. Sprinkle with cheese; cover with remaining buttered bread slices. Cut hamwiches diagonally.
(At this point, may be covered and refrigerated overnight.) Combine eggs, milk and salt and pour over bread.
Chill 1 hour.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice (preferably the day before and keep in fridge overnight; otherwise, allow cooked rice to cool).
Finely slice bacon and chop onion and green pepper. Set aside.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: In 10-inch covered skillet over medium heat, cook sausage and 2 tablespoons water for 5 minutes.
Uncover; cook until sausage is browned on all sides.
Add green peppers, onion and garlic; cook until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in soup, 1/2 cup water and basil; reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: summer sausage
directions: Add liquid smoke to water and mix well with hamburg before adding dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 2 or 3 rolls and put each in foil, shiny side towards meat.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Before baking, punch holes in bottom of each roll.
Put on rack so grease may drain while baking.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix sugar and flour; stir into melted butter.
Stir in milk, eggs and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in corn.
Pour mixture into 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake until top is golden brown and center is set, about 45 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish. Place covered in oven and bake at 450° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and stir well.
Continue baking uncovered at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until pepper is soft.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, orange, apples and pineapple.
Add sugar. Let stand 24 hours or more.

title: tamale pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add ground beef, chili powder, cumin and salt and pepper to taste.
Add green olives with pimentos and tomato sauce.
Bring 1 1/2 quarts water to boil.
When boiling, add 1 1/2 cups yellow cornmeal.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour half of cornmeal mixture into 9 x 13 baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Add all of meat mixture, then put rest of cornmeal mix on top of meat.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: whipped honey lemon yogurt
directions: Mix together the yogurt, honey, lemon rind and juice.
Beat the egg white until stiff and fold into yogurt mixture.
Spoon into 4 glasses and top each with thin curls of lemon rind.
Serve chilled.
Serves 4.

title: zesty jalapeno squares
directions: Spray a 9 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam.
Line bottom of pan with jalapenos, approximately 1 per bite.
Beat eggs and pour over jalapenos.
Sprinkle grated cheese over eggs.
Sprinkle salsa over grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Wait 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: clark bar peanut butter candy
directions: Spread peanut butter on a small cookie sheet.
Boil Karo syrup, sugar and water to 300°.
Pour over peanut butter and stir. Pour onto another cookie sheet.
When hard cut into strips and pieces.

title: my party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: watergate salad or pistachio salad
directions: Mix ingredients, chill and enjoy.

title: poppy seed cake #1
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, vegetable oil, eggs and instant pudding, then add water, poppy seed and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Place batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from pan (if difficult, wait 1 or 2 minutes more). Invert onto plate and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: delicious spice tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix together coconut, sour cream and sugar the night before you make the cake.
Leave in refrigerator.
Make cake by the directions on the Duncan Hines yellow cake mix box.
Bake in two cake pans. After cake cools, slice the layers in half, will be four layers instead of two.
Ice all four on tops and sides.
Refrigerate for four days, then it's ready to eat or this cake freezes well after it's been in refrigerator for 4 days.

title: quick chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet over high heat.
Cut chicken into strips. Add to skillet with garlic; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add vegetables; stir-fry an additional 3 minutes. Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in Miracle Whip, soy sauce and ginger. Simmer 1 minute.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: nankipoo salsa
directions: Cook over
medium heat until comes to a boil.
Place in warm, clean jars (pint).
Process in water (boil) 40 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Gradually add oil and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: athenian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover bottom of pan with very thin layer of olive oil.
Place chicken in pan and squeeze lemon on each piece.
Season each piece with oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Place a thin pat of butter on top of each piece of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and water.
Cook until dissolved. Add jello and berries.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: one dish meat loaf, potatoes and vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes, peas and tomato soup. Shape into a large, deep ring.
Put frozen peas in center of ring. Put potatoes around outside of ring.
(If potatoes are large, cut in half.)
Mix soup with equal amount of milk; pour over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours, or until potatoes are done.

title: chess pie squares
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 egg and margarine together.
Press in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Blend the cream cheese, 3 eggs and vanilla together until smooth.
Slowly mix in powdered sugar until smooth. Pour over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 55 to 60 minutes, or until top is golden brown.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Use fresh, firm cucumbers; wash and cut into sticks.
Pour boiling water over them and let stand 4 to 5 hours.
Pack solidly into jars.
Boil solution for 5 minutes.
Pour boiling hot over cucumbers in jars.
Put lids on tightly.
Fills 6 pints.

title: crepes
directions: Mix until smooth. Bake on both sides until browned in small greased skillet. Batter is thin. Pour just a little in skillet and tilt until it covers the bottom. Grease or oil again for next crepe.

title: roast raccoon with gravy
directions: Rub the raccoon with salt and pepper.
Cut small slits in the animal and insert garlic slivers into these.
Place on a rack in a roasting pan and roast about 3 hours at 300° while basting with the drippings every half hour or so.

title: cheesy chili casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add pepper and onion. Saute. Stir in corn, sauce and chili powder. Add 1/2 cup cheese spread.
Stir until melted. Spread 1 cup meat mixture onto bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with 1 cup chips.
Repeat layering twice. Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining chips, tomato and cheese spread.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: favorite squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole dish and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: friendship recipe
directions: Stir it all together.
Put it in the oven to bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle it with self control.
Then you have a good friendship.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix everything just until blended.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425° (goes great with chili).

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add beaten eggs, bananas and vanilla; beat well.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 1/2-inches apart.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° about 12 minutes.
Remove cookies from pan immediately.

title: chocolatetown pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell. Set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a small mixer bowl, cream the butter.
Add eggs and vanilla or bourbon.
Combine sugar and flour. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden. Cool 1 hour. Serve warm. Garnish with festive whipped cream.

title: steak marinade
directions: Sprinkle garlic powder lightly on both sides of steak.
Prick both sides with fork.
Combine soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and oil.
Pour over steak.
Marinate 6 to 8 hours turning frequently.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into greased and floured bread pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: my favorite cake
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and eggs together; add flour, salt and vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° to 350°.
Best eaten while warm.

title: veal ala parmesan
directions: Bread chops or cutlets and brown.
Saute vegetables with 2 tablespoons fat.
Add tomato sauce.
Place chops in baking pan and use 1/2 vegetable mixture to cover.
Add thin layer of Mozzarella cheese and rest of vegetables over cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Good.

title: jane anne's broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix with other ingredients (save small amount of cheese for top).
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix. Put half in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon in softened ice cream.
Pour remaining Chex mix over top and freeze. Cut in squares.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables separately and drain. Do not overcook.
Mix mayonnaise with other ingredients and let stand at least 6 hours. Mix with vegetables and let stand 24 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix cooked macaroni, vegetables and salad dressing together. Serve chilled.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Cook rice. Brown meat and onions; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce; cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Place in a shallow pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Chill 30 to 45 minutes.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut and bake until slightly golden color.
Bake at 400°.

title: mongolian chinese beer beef dukiyaki
directions: Brown beef in oil. Add vegetables, broth and other seasonings. Simmer 20 minutes. Add cornstarch and cook until thick.

title: onion bread
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Combine with mix just until blended. Spoon into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese and let set at room temperature until soft.
Blend Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and pimento together.
Add all other ingredients and beat until smooth.
I use a mixer.
You can use food processor.

title: sugarless apple crisp
directions: Put cut up apples in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with tablespoon of liquid artificial sweetener, lemon juice and cinnamon. Combine last 4 ingredients in separate bowl.
Toss with fork and blend well. Sprinkle over apples. Pour 3/4 cup hot water over topping. Cover and bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: danish coffee
directions: Chill bowl and beater.
In medium saucepan, mix chocolate, water, sugar, coffee and salt.
Set over low heat, stirring until chocolate melts and comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir constantly while adding milk.
Return to heat until scalded, not boiled.
Beat whipping cream in well-chilled bowl until cream stands in peaks.
Serve coffee piping hot, each serving topped with whipped cream.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients well.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Press into sugar and bake 9 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix margarine and corn flakes.
Place half of mixture in pan. Spread cabbage and onions.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over cabbage.
Shred cheese over soup mixture.
Spread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot jello
directions: Bring Jell-O, sugar and water to boil, then add cream cheese, apricot baby food
and crushed pineapple; not drained.
Set aside and let cool.

title: microwave peanut butter eggs
directions: In 1 1/2-quart bowl or casserole, microwave margarine at High for 1 to 2 minutes, until melted.
Add crumbs, sugar and peanut butter; mix well.
Chill until firm.
Shape into eggs and refrigerate.
Microwave chocolate chips in covered casserole at Medium for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring every two minutes, until completely melted.
Using toothpicks, dip eggs into melted chocolate to coat.
Chill eggs on cookie sheet until firm.

title: cranberry crimson mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Gradually whisk salad dressing into gelatin until smooth.
Stir in cranberry orange sauce and applesauce.
Pour into a 5-cup ring mold which has been sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: dirty rice
directions: Break up sausage with a fork and cook until brown in a large heavy pot.
Add chopped bell pepper, green onions and garlic. Saute until soft.
Stir in uncooked rice and salt.
Put in casserole dish and add broth.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes, until liquid has been absorbed.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake, uncovered, in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk in saucepan until a little dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and coconut.
Beat until thick.
Pour in pan to cool.

title: shortcake(for strawberries or raspberries)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix oil, vanilla and sugar until light and fluffy.
Combine with flour mixture.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add milk.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil. Boil 90 seconds. Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter. Mix well. Add Special K cereal, mixing well. Drop by spoon onto wax paper. Makes 38 to 40 pieces.

title: chicken soup
directions: Combine the first six ingredients in Dutch oven.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Remove skin and bone from chicken and return meat to broth.
Add 1 cup frozen peas.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Boil 1 qt. of milk.
Set aside.
Mix flour, salt and 1/2 c. sugar with enough milk to make a paste.
Beat eggs and add to mixture and add to boiled milk.
Run through strainer.
Pour into a 4 qt. freezer.
Add sugar, syrup and remaining milk.
Add vanilla and freeze.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add grated Cheddar, onion dip, onion salt and and garlic salt to taste.
Form into ball and refrigerate.
When chilled, roll in crushed pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Debone cooked chicken.
Mix together soups and sour cream, adding one can of chicken broth.
Place egg noodles into the pot you boiled the chicken in.
You may have to add some water to the chicken broth to cook the noodles tender.
When noodles are tender, mix together with mixture and chicken.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Roast or cook chicken.
Let cool.
Pick meat from bones and chop fine.
Chop gherkins and celery.
Add to chicken, along with pickle juice, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and hard-boiled eggs.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine and cook onions.
Butter a casserole dish and line with cracker crumbs.
Add onion and soup in layers until dish is full.
Beat eggs and add to milk.
Pour over the casserole ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell and reserve remaining pastry for lattice top.
Drain peaches thoroughly and set aside.
Sift together in a bowl the sugar, cornstarch, spices and salt.
Add cream and lemon juice gradually, blending until smooth.
Gently mix in peaches. Turn filling into pastry shell, top with pastry strips to form lattice design.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until pastry is light brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Pears may also be used.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir only until mixed well. Mixture may be lumpy.
Pour into a loaf pan that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili cheese casserole
directions: Place chilies in baking dish, cover with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, flour, and salt.
Pour over chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is gone.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add cooled raisins.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes about six dozen cookies.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add the first 2 ingredients and let cool.
Beat the next 3 together.
Add all the rest together and then put in the All-Bran mixture last.
Add raisins, dates and nuts.
Spray muffin tins with Pam and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over salad and mix.

title: navajo fry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add lard until mixture is like coarse crumbs.
Stir in water. Knead on floured surface. Divide dough into balls. Cover and let rest. Roll each ball into flat circle. Make hole in center.
Fry each one in hot fat until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Makes about 8.

title: easiest chocolate mousse
directions: In a small saucepan, heat heavy cream until warm, not hot. Combine egg, vanilla and chips in a blender.
Do not blend until cream is added.
When cream is warm, add to blender and mix on high for 30 to 45 seconds.
Pour mixture into dessert cups and chill. Makes approximately 4 (1/4 cup) servings.

title: holiday crab dip
directions: Blend together first five ingredients.
Fold in the rest of the ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise,
chicken bouillon, vinegar, sugar and water. Pour over onions, celery, eggs, potatoes and 3/4 of the bacon. Sprinkle remaining bacon on top.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Boil peppers for 5 minutes.
Mix hamburger, onion, pepper, salt and 1 can of tomato sauce together.
After peppers boil for 5 minutes, stuff hamburger ingredients inside boiled peppers.
Pour 3 cans of tomato sauce over stuffed peppers.
Bake at 350° until hamburger meat is done (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes. Mix first 8 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole. Melt the 1/4 cup butter and mix crushed corn flakes with the butter. Put over top and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar in bowl.
Add eggs; beating well. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix just until smooth.
Stir in oats, coconuts and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: seasoned green beans
directions: Open can of green beans.
Put in saucepan.
Add 1 can water, onion and beef bouillon.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and cook for about 1 hour.
Liquid should be almost cooked away.
Serves 2.

title: rudolph sandwiches
directions: Cut the bread from corner to corner. Cover with peanut butter. Put on raisins for eyes.
Give him a red cherry nose.
Make antlers with the pretzels.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients into blender.
Blend on high for 1 minute.
Pour into tall glass and enjoy.

title: collard greens
directions: Wash and cut greens into 3/4-inch slices. Put 1 1/2 quarts water into pressure cooker, bring to boil. Drop greens into boiling water and stir occasionally until all greens are wilted. Remove from heat and pour off water. When all water is removed, add 1/2 cup water, salt to taste and the drippings and oil. Stir until well coated. Put pressure on greens and when pressure is up, cook 5 minutes. Let pressure go down and stir. Serve hot.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and syrup, then eggs, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked crust and bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Fix jello as always and let cool; whip until foamy.
Cream together sugar, cheese and jello.
Whip can of chilled milk; add to other ingredients, folding in.
Add vanilla.
Place in a graham cracker crust, saving some crumbs to spread over top.
Pour jello mix over crust.
Put in refrigerator and let set for 12 hours.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons water.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Batter will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: betsy's prime rib
directions: Set thawed roast out at room temperature for 4 hours before cooking.
Put in oven, fat side up.
No water, no cover, no salt, no basting.

title: crabmeat rounds
directions: Mix well and spread on Melba or garlic rounds. Broil until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: sherrie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening and eggs.
Make into small patty cakes.
Bake in a 400° oven for approximately 4 to 5 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti southwest style
directions: Bring a large pot of water to boil for pasta.
Add salt and cook until al dente; drain.
Beat together the milk and egg and mix with hot pasta.
Spread mixture in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish (3-quart).

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Rub into brisket nutmeg, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Bake for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain off stock.
Cool meat, then slice across grain, very thin.
Arrange meat in casserole dish.
Mix and pour over sliced meat the catsup, vinegar, water, sauce, brown sugar and liquid smoke.
Return to oven and reheat for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate for 24 hours.
Meat can be cooked in an oven on racks at 150° for 7 hours or for best results, use a dehydrator.
Cook 4 to 5 hours at top temperature, turning once during cooking time.
Jerky should be pliable but dry when done.
Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator. (Works well with venison and turkey, too.)

title: 5 minute clam and parsley pasta sauce
directions: Crush the garlic.
Fry the garlic and loosely chopped parsley for 2 minutes in the olive oil.
Add clams, including juice, lemon juice and pepper.
Serve over pasta.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Beat well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch floured pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: one dish chicken broccoli rice
directions: In large skillet in hot margarine, cook chicken until browned. Add broccoli and carrots.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice.
Cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: brownie mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.

title: zesty baked flounder
directions: Rub mayonnaise on both sides of flounder.
Place on broiler pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle cheese on each side of flounder.
Bake at 350° to 400° until tender and light brown. Flounder should be flaky.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham crackers and 1 stick melted butter in mixing bowl. Press into bottom of 9 x 13 cake pan.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and store.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: praline dream pie
directions: Heat nuts, margarine and sugar in small saucepan until margarine and sugar are melted and mixture comes to boil.
Boil 30 seconds.
Spread on bottom of shell and cool.
Beat whipped topping, 1 cup milk and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer on high speed about 6 minutes or until topping thickens and forms peaks.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix; blend on low speed. Beat on high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until ready to serve.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: saucy baked beans
directions: Saute onions and bacon in large saucepan until lightly browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer at least 15 minutes, stirring occasionally (or bring mixture to a boil, then pour into casserole or baking pan and bake at 425° for about 1 hour or until bubbly).

title: light corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar and salt. In separate bowl, lightly beat buttermilk and eggs. Beat in baking soda, followed by the melted shortening. Combine egg mixture with dry ingredients, blending lightly but thoroughly. Do not overbeat. Divide batter between 2 greased 9 x 5 loaf pans. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix first 5
ingredients. Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot. Serve with crackers or toasted pita bread.

title: nut bread(norway)
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
Add nuts and dates.
Combine liquids; stir into first mixture.
Stir.
Turn into three Number 2 size greased cans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn tins on sides during last 15 minutes.
To remove from tins, cut out bottoms of cans.
Nice for holiday gifts!

title: sauerkraut apple relish
directions: Add sugar and vinegar together to dissolve.
Add apples and sauerkraut.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Overnight is best.
Stir a few times. Flavor improves on standing.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving breadcrumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter for topping.
Put into well-greased casserole dish. Combine breadcrumbs and butter; crumble on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In blender, process oatmeal until powdery.
In a separate bowl, combine oatmeal, flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and chopped nuts.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 minutes.
(Bake only six minutes; cookies will not seem done, but will set.)
Yield:
50 to 60 large cookies.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Place cheeses in mixing bowl and allow to soften to room temperature. Add onion and Worcestershire sauce and beat until fluffy. Shape into large ball and roll in finely chopped nuts. Cover and refrigerate. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: corn muffins
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well.
Add other ingredients.
Beat well. Pour into greased muffin pan, 1/2 full each.
Bake at 400° until just golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake in 325° oven 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: zucchini and tomato soup
directions: Microwave 18 minutes, stirring periodically the first 7 ingredients or simmer 10 minutes or until done, then add remaining ingredients and microwave 1 1/2 minutes or simmer 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Serves 4.
Calories 40, cholesterol 1 mg and fat 1 g.

title: pure fruit wedding punch
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice and freeze.
When ready to use, take out 2 hours before serving.
Right before serving, chop frozen ingredients and add ginger ale.
Makes 30 (6 ounce) cups.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt Hershey bars in chocolate syrup over low heat and let cool.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift flour; add soda and sift again.
Add flour, soda and buttermilk to sugar/butter mixture.
Fold in vanilla and chocolate syrup.
Pour into large Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: chicken cashew casserole(serves 15)
directions: Combine; pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle extra noodles on top before serving.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Roll in flour and brown in hot oil. In a buttered baking dish, spread the rice.
Chop garlic and mince onion, spreading both over rice.
Arrange browned beef over this and pour consomme and water over all.
Salt and pepper as desired. Spread can of mushrooms, with liquid, over all and bake in a covered dish for 1 hour at 325°.

title: wedding cake
directions: Beat egg whites, adding about 1/2 cup sugar, until stiffly beaten.
Cream sugar and Crisco together well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with the milk to the creamed sugar mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Fold in the egg whites. Pour batter into a 14-inch, a 12-inch and an 8-inch greased and floured cake pan for a tiered Wedding Cake.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: yu nien-tze chang's chow mein(fried noodles)
directions: Shred cabbage. Cut chicken into short, thin strips.
Dice green pepper.
Cut mushroom pieces into thin strips.
cook spaghetti, only until firm; drain.
Heat peanut oil in wok. Stir-fry meat, cabbage, green pepper, bean sprouts and mushroom pieces.
Chop up spaghetti and add to other ingredients in the wok.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add soy sauce until light brown color is achieved.
Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Heat until warm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: old-time turkey bake(quickie)
directions: Prepare gravy mix, increasing water to 1 1/4 cups.
Stir in the diced cooked turkey and the frozen peas.
Heat to boiling. Spoon into casserole dish.
Top with refrigerator biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: taco sauce
directions: Mix all together and bring to boil; simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with lettuce, tomato, cheese, relish or any other topping with hamburger in tortilla shells.

title: gala cheesecake
directions: Warm cream cheese, sour cream, butter and eggs until room temperature. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a large bowl, whip cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in butter and sour cream, then add cornstarch, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice. At high speed, beat mixture until very well blended. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Pour cheesecake batter into a well-buttered 10 inch spring form pan. Place pan in a larger pan and add enough warm water to come halfway up side of pan.

title: nelma's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni per package directions.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk and cook mixture until thickened slightly.
Add cheese.
Stir into milk mixture. Pour over cooked and drained macaroni.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. The best macaroni and cheese you'll ever eat!

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt butter and saute vegetables.
Stir in flour and cornstarch.
Add stock and milk, gradually blending into a smooth sauce.
Add soda and cheese and stir until thickened.
Add salt, pepper and parsley.
Do not boil.
Garnish with paprika.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry burritos
directions: Cut skinless chicken into small, 1-inch pieces.
Season chicken with lemon pepper.
Heat small amount of oil or butter (1 to 2 tablespoons) in a large skillet; add chicken.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add stir-fry vegetables.
Cook an additional 4 to 5 minutes.
Add stir-fry sauce.
Fill tortilla shell with desired amount of chicken/vegetable mixture.
Fry tortillas in small amount of butter.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Add broken pecans and dot with 1/4 stick oleo; pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: travis' favorite pita pizzas
directions: On a large cookie sheet, place uncut pita breads.
Spread pizza sauce; top with pepperoni, grated cheese and chopped olives.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pookie louise green chile corn bread
directions: Mix everything together and put in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown the meat until crumbly in a large pot.
Add celery, onions, tomatoes and beans and simmer until celery is soft.
In the meantime, boil noodles in 3 quarts salted water for 15 minutes; drain.
Combine all in a large casserole.
Brown bread squares or Kellogg's croutons and sprinkle over casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes, until bread is browned.

title: john's easy pie crust
directions: Cut lard or shortening into small chunks.
Pour boiling water over this and stir into a creamy mass.
Add salt and sugar. Stir sifted flour and baking powder into mixture.
Use a cutting motion until it is well blended.
Gently shape into large ball; wrap in wax paper and set in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: In a heavy bottom 2-quart saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add milk and cubed cream cheese, stirring over medium heat until the cream cheese has melted.
Stir in cubed processed cheese, cooked and drained broccoli and seasonings.
Heat through gently.
Makes 5 cups soup.

title: chocolate delight dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine, nuts and the 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool 45 minutes.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk. Stir in cheese and onions.
Fold in crabmeat.
Season to taste.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Shape into balls.
Pour sauce over meatballs and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: kelly's chicken stuff
directions: Preheat oven 400°.
In frying pan brown cubed chicken, add seasoning salt and 1/4 cup water turn down burner to low and cover.
In large mixing bowl combine soup, milk and green peppers. When chicken is done add to soup mixture.
Line a 9 X 13 greased pan with layer of corn chips.
Then spoon on soup and chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese (about 1/3 of a pound).
Repeat. Then cover with a layer of chips and the rest of the cheese.
Cook for 15-20 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: mom's in a hurry casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and salt; drain.
Mix browned hamburger, potatoes, soup, sour cream, cheese and chopped onion.
Mix well. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with fried onions.
Bake 15 minutes more or until bubbly.

title: coconut and pecan frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes. Add the coconut and pecans.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Makes 2 1/2 cups and enough to ice a German chocolate cake.

title: old fashioned johnnycake
directions: Beat
with beater until smooth (about 1 minute).
Don't overbeat.
Bake
in greased 8-inch square pan in 425° hot oven (preheat) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.	Serve hot. Good with syrup or jelly.

title: punch
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Mix sugar and water.
Mix everything together and freeze in 3 containers, 7 2/3 cups to each. To serve mix one container plus 1 (3 liter) Sprite.
Yield:
3 bowls.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut in Crisco with flour with a fork.
Add other ingredients. Roll out and cut.
Place on greased pan.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix together and pour over meat and refrigerate for 4 hours. For beef, marinate overnight.
Turn several times.
Amount good for 4 steaks; for more than 4 steaks, double
the recipe.

title: ziti bake
directions: Boil ziti until tender.
Brown ground beef.
Remove from heat, stir in Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, egg, salt and pepper.
Add ziti and half of spaghetti sauce.
Toss to cook well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with rest of sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until Mozzarella is melted.
Serves 8.

title: gelatin "blocks" for snacks or treats
directions: In a large bowl, combine all gelatins; add boiling water and stir until dissolved completely.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.
Cut with a knife into bite size "blocks" or cut with cookie cutters for different shapes.

title: cauliflower and broccoli dish
directions: Mix until melted and thickened.
Heat oven to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Add bananas by hand.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot applesauce
directions: Combine applesauce, horseradish and nutmeg in blender or food processor.
Whirl.
Place in a saucepan and heat.
Serve in small bowl.
Especially good with pork or ham.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. In large soup pot, add beef and diced potatoes. Cover potatoes with water. Cook 20 minutes on medium heat. Quarter cabbage and add to pot. Cook until cabbage is tender. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in loaf pans.
Bake about 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Place on racks to cool.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: quick soup
directions: Divide corn, pepper and cheese between 4 large coffee mugs. Heat tomato juice to a boil.
Pour into mugs.
Put 1 bread stick in each mug and serve.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; simmer for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally. Pour into 6 quart jars and seal, then process in pressure canner at 5 pounds for 10 minutes.

title: sandwich spread to can
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Wash; pour hot water over peppers and squeeze.
Make a paste of sugar, mustard, flour and salt.
Add peppers and onions; boil 10 minutes.
Stir in mayonnaise; bring to boil.
Can and seal like canning any vegetables.
Be sure it seals; will keep for months.
Serve alone or with meat or sliced cheese.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Roll all ingredients together into balls.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Can be frozen.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pat out in bottom of cookie sheet pan with sides.
Mix last four ingredients and pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve hot or cool.

title: no bake raisin sour cream pie
directions: Blend together the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Combine with beaten eggs, sour cream, raisins, grated lemon rind and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over hot water until thick.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into baked shell.
Sprinkle top with additional grated lemon rind, if desired.

title: baked fish
directions: Clean fish and cut into servings or cut in half down the back. Season and sprinkle with cracker meal.
Heat oil in pan or roaster in oven (450°).
Add fish to hot oil.
Cook, uncovered; baste it with the oil to brown nicely.
When brown, drain off oil. Cover the fish; return to oven and turn off and let fish steam for 25 to 40 minutes.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: chicken parmegiana
directions: Place chicken breasts on cutting board and pound lightly with cleaver until 1/4-inch thick. Combine eggs, salt and pepper. Dip chicken into mixture, then crumbs. Heat oil until very hot in a large frying pan. Quickly brown chicken on both sides, remove to shallow baking dish. Pour excess oil from frying pan. Stir tomato sauce, basil and garlic powder into frying pan. Heat to boiling, simmer 10 minutes, or until thickened. Stir in butter. Pour sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and cover. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, then uncover. Place Mozzarella cheese over chicken. Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and debone.
Add chicken soup and other ingredients, except taco chips and cheese.
Put taco chips on bottom of oblong dish.
Top with chicken mixture, then with cheese.
Place in oven, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated beef kabobs
directions: Using small holes of hand grater, grate orange peel.
Cut orange into quarters.
In medium glass or stainless steel mixing bowl, combine orange quarters, orange peel, beef, mushrooms and scallions.
In a 1-cup liquid measure, combine remaining ingredients, except cornstarch.
Add to beef mixture; toss to coat.
Cover; refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: yogurt cucumber sauce
directions: Wash and grate cucumber.
Combine yogurt, cucumber and spice in small bowl.

title: cinnamon decorator dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Take a small amount of dough and flatten.
Cut out shapes with cookie cutters.
If planning on hanging decorations, punch hole by sticking a cut up drinking straw through the top.
Allow dough to dry for 48 hours.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and basil.
Stir in chicken broth and cook until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add chicken.
Mix cottage cheese with beaten egg.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Take the sugar, hot water and syrup and let boil until forms a little hard ball.
Beat egg whites separately.
Pour sugar mixture in egg whites.
Roll out.
Put peanut butter in warm water; spread on mixture.
(Guess at peanut butter, 2 to 3 tablespoons.)

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix, frosting, eggs, oil, water and pecans with mixer. Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hot fruit
directions: Combine oleo, sugar, flour and wine and bring to boil.
Pour over drained fruit and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bavarian pound cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well; then add coconut and pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pack into loaf pan.

title: potato cabbage casserole
directions: Place potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add onion, salt, pepper and cabbage.
Top with sliced corned beef.
Mix soup and milk and pour over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: flour tortilla appetizers
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients. Spread mixture on tortillas and roll up. Chill for at least 2 hours, then cut in 1-inch slices.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a large kettle, cook beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients in this order: tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, cumin, paprika, basil and cocoa.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: honey glazed chicken wings
directions: Split wings at each joint; discard tips.
Sprinkle seasoned salt and garlic on wings.
Combine flour and paprika in paper bag. Add wings; shake well to coat.
Drop and fry wings in 400° oil for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 2 minutes, stirring, until thicken. Place wings on baking sheet.
Pour sauce over wings; bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger-tater tot casserole
directions: Line bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish with frozen Tater Tots. Brown hamburger; drain and spread over Tater Tots.
Mix cheese soup and milk together; pour over hamburger.
Dot top of casserole with a few Tater Tots; sprinkle shredded cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until bubbling.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Mix together cranberries, sugar and pineapple.
Let set for 12 hours.
Then add Cool Whip and miniature marshmallows and nuts, if desired.

title: banana macadamia nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter, eggs, baking soda, salt, orange peel and vanilla.
Beat at low speed, scraping often for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add bananas and orange juice.
Continue beating until well mixed (1 minute).
By hand, stir in coconut and nuts.
Spread into 1 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or 3 (5 1/2 x 3-inch) greased mini loaf pans.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers, celery and green onion in margarine or butter.
Place in a large greased casserole with all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 400° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Slice bananas on top of mixture.
Pour pineapple on top of bananas.
Whip the Dream Whip and put on top of pineapple. Garnish with maraschino cherries and nuts.
Chill for a short time.

title: rich's chili
directions: Cook meat until brown. Drain off grease. Add onion and some chili powder to meat while it cooks. Combine meat and other ingredients in a large cooking pot. DO NOT add any beans to this recipe. Bring chili to boil and reduce heat to simmer. Stir often, tasting for the right flavor. Let chili age before serving. Preferable 4 to 6 hours.

title: roast turkey
directions: Wash turkey; remove giblets.
Separate skin from breast and push slices of onion and pieces of celery into spaces.
Fill all other cavities with celery and onion after rubbing with spices.

title: banana molasses bread
directions: Stir, don't beat.
Mash bananas (no lumps).
Add unbeaten egg; mix.
Beat in sugar, molasses and shortening.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan in a 325° oven for about 1 hour.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Fry wings or bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes, then check for doneness.
Mix dry salad mix, melted margarine, lemon juice and hot sauce.
Pour mixture over cooked wings.
Spread wings on cookie sheet in single layer.
Bake 10 to 20 minutes until lightly brown and crisp.

title: white grape punch
directions: Combine apple juice, grape juice and lemonade; chill well. Stir in club soda when ready to serve.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.
