title: easy peach pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
If they are bitter, add some sugar. Melt the butter in baking dish.
Put fruit on top.
Pour batter on fruit. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand in the refrigerator for 24 hours before using.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Use as needed, as the batter keeps, refrigerated, for 1 month.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Chop ingredients.
Add to cooked macaroni with mayonnaise and mustard.
Salt to taste.
Garnish with sliced, hard-boiled eggs.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine flours and remaining dry ingredients in a bowl.
In a second bowl, combine milk with eggs, then oil, then apples and raisins.
Add dry ingredients.
Place tablespoon of batter in 375° oil.
Turn in oil until golden brown.
Serve with maple syrup or powdered sugar.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add water and bouillon cubes; bring to a boil.
Add noodles and salt; bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder; cook 4 minutes.
Add milk and heat on low until hot.
Add cheese and heat on low until cheese is melted.
Gets better after reheating.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.

title: strawberry-rhubarb cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with rhubarb.
Sprinkle Jell-O over rhubarb.
Sprinkle sugar over Jell-O.
Cover with marshmallows.
Pour cake batter over this.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Use large pot deep enough so you can put lid on over cabbage. Bring water to a boil.
Put cabbage in and let stand for 1 hour. Mix all other ingredients, then put in cabbage leaf.
Roll and put toothpick through.
Place in pot.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cook about 3 hours on low heat or overnight in crock-pot.

title: yabba-dabba-doo squares
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, stirring frequently.
Add marshmallows and cereal.
Stir until marshmallows start to melt and stick to cereal.
Remove from heat.
Press mixture firmly into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill about 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Store in cool place.
Makes 16 squares.

title: oven-fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow dish or zip top bag. Dip tomato slices in water; dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Spray a baking sheet.
Place tomato slices on pan.
Coat each slice with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Contains 1.1 gram of fat.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a pie plate (10 x 1 1/2 inches). Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate.
Beat the milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute in mixer.
Pour in plate.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomato (if desired) and cheese.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients. Press into jelly roll pan that has been buttered. Beat remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over cake already in pan. Bake at 350° (not on lowest rack) about 25 to 30 minutes. Top should be golden brown. Dip knife in water for easier cutting. Freezes well!

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, bell pepper, garlic and salt.
Set aside.
Wash and peel eggplant; slice into rounds.
Dip into beaten egg and roll in crumbs.
Melt butter, 1/4 stick at a time, in a skillet and brown eggplant on both sides.
Put eggplant in casserole dish, add a layer of meat mixture, cover with tomato sauce and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken caliente
directions: In 13 x 9 casserole, place layer of chicken (1/2) - sprinkle with half the chili powder and garlic salt, then 1/2 of soup mixture (soups, broth, tomatoes). Then layer of tortillas. Top with 1/2 the onion, green pepper and grated cheese. Repeat layers. Bake covered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Serves 6 - 8.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Partially thaw strawberries.
Add to jello dissolved in water.
Add nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set 1/2 hour in refrigerator.
Add sour cream, then remaining jello.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine sliced berries, sugar or honey and orange juice. Let stand
at room temperature for 1 hour.
Sift all dry ingredients together
into
a
medium
bowl.
Add orange rind.
Add butter and
shortening
and work them into flour mixture thoroughly. Lightly
mix
in
sour
cream with fork to form a soft dough. Roll
dough
out
onto
lightly floured board, 3/4-inch thick. Cut
into
4-inches,
circles.
Place
on
ungreased baking sheet,
bake
at
400° about 20 minutes or until golden. While still
warm, use fork and split cakes in half, place each on dessert
plate,
top with drained berries and second half of cake. Top
with
additional berries.
Pour juice on top, decorate with whipped cream and berries.

title: cream of tartar pickles
directions: Cut tips off cucumbers and quarter lengthwise.
Put in jars with dill and onion slices.
Boil syrup and pour over cucumbers hot.
Liquid covers 4 quarts.

title: candy bar pie
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Crush the candy bars; fold 1 cup into the cream cheese mixture. Spoon into crust. Sprinkle with remaining candy bar crumbs. Refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours before slicing. Serves 6 or 8.

title: lemon gelatin salad(serves 16)
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on package using juice as part of water.
Mix other ingredients with Jell-O.
Let set several hours or overnight.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine and beat; put in large cookie sheet with sides and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta with shrimp and jalapeno-orange sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add shrimp and cook until just pink (about 1 minute per side).
Transfer shrimp to plate.
Add shallots and jalapeno to skillet and saute 1 minute.
Add wine; bring to a boil.
Mix in orange juice and cream; boil until reduced to thin sauce, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Can be prepared 4 hours ahead.
Cover and refrigerate shrimp and sauce separately.
Cook pasta.
Bring sauce to simmer and add shrimp.
Serve over pasta.

title: baked apple pancakes
directions: Combine pancake mix, oil, milk and egg. In cast-iron skillet, melt butter. Add brown sugar and apple. Pour batter over butter mixture and cook until bubbles come to top. Move skillet to preheated 350° oven and cook for 12 to 17 minutes. Invert pancake onto platter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and salt together and add remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Makes two pies.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Cut apples into small pieces.
Put a layer of apples and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar, then a layer of batter, then apples, cinnamon-sugar, batter, then more apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check with toothpick or cake tester after 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexicali spaghetti bake
directions: Cook spaghetti as package directs; drain.
Heat oven to 325°. Saute ground chuck until partially browned.
Add onions, peppers and garlic.
When meat is browned, add spaghetti, tomatoes, corn, salt, black pepper, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Toss and turn into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients and combine with green beans.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Prepare 24 hours before serving.

title: corn salad
directions: In a bowl, combine vegetables.
Stir in dressing.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: company spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain after beef has cooked.
Add soup, tomatoes, half and half and Velveeta.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add mixture to cooked spaghetti.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated Longhorn cheese.

title: stromboli
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, green pepper, tomato sauce and oregano.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Make jello per package instructions.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple to jello.
Add marshmallows.
After jello is set, put on topping of 1 cup Miracle Whip and 1 cup whipped cream (mixed). Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: hellmann's amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside apples, raisins and nuts.
In a large mixer bowl, mix remaining ingredients at low speed for about 2 minutes, scraping bowl.
(The batter will be very thick.)
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins. Spoon into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered ravioli meat loaf casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, egg, onions, salt, crumbs, milk, parsley and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Divide into thirds.
Spread 1/3 meat mixture on bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Arrange one can of beef ravioli on top of meat, then another third of meat mixture.
Top with second can of ravioli. Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Serves six.

title: devilish chocolate cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
In second bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, salt and powdered oats.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture in small batches.
Blend all well.
Stir in chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pork with clams
directions: Marinade:
Combine wine, garlic and salt in medium-size glass bowl.
Cut pork in 1-inch cubes; add to marinade, turning pork to cover.
Store overnight in refrigerator; turn meat occasionally.

title: sweet and sour stuffed cabbage
directions: Place cabbage leaves in boiling water until wilted.
Season meat, egg and rice.
Roll a portion of meat mixture in each cabbage leaf.
Place rolls in skillet with the rest of ingredients and simmer until sauce thickens and cabbage is tender.

title: apple and blue cheese salad
directions: In salad bowl, beat together sour cream, mayonnaise, Blue cheese, lemon juice, celery salt and pepper until well blended. Fold in apples and celery.
Sprinkle with walnuts; serve on greens.
Serves 4.

title: frank's shrimp creole
directions: Cook in deep frypan (electric or regular).
Add butter and melt.
Add onions, celery, okra, garlic, green pepper and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Add tomatoes and tomato paste; cover and simmer for about 10 minutes over medium heat.
Stir.
Add shrimp.
Serve over hot rice.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring ham and bacon to a boil; add potatoes, carrots and onions.
Cook approximately 20 minutes.
Add the rest of ingredients, cook until done.
Season to taste.
This is better the next day.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Measure all ingredients into blender jar (or a deep cup if using a hand held blender).
Blend on medium speed until mixture reaches desired consistency (30 to 40 seconds).
If using hand held blender, start with blades on the bottom of the cup and pull up through the mixture slowly with blender on medium speed.

title: snow tunnel cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. Slice 1-inch layer off the top.
Gently hollow out a trench in the cake, 1 1/2-inches deep.
Tear cake pieces from trench into small pieces.
Combine milk and pudding mix. Fold cake pieces and 1 3/4 cups topping into pudding mix. Fill trench with mixture.
Replace top of cake. Spread remaining topping over sides and top. Chill until set.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: waldorf rice salad
directions: Combine oranges, apple, pear, rice, celery and craisins in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream; add to rice mixture. Cover and chill.
spoon salad mixture onto individual plates or into lettuce lined bowl.
Sprinkle with walnuts just before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana fruit bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in beaten egg and fruit. Stir in dry ingredients, alternately with liquid.
Blend in nuts. Pour batter into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 9x13 pan.
Bake at 375° for 4 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Arrange strawberries, bananas and pineapple in even layers.
Prepare pudding with the 3 cups cold milk as directed and pour over fruit.
Chill several hours.
Before serving spread remaining Cool Whip on top and decorate with extra strawberries.

title: custard pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix all ingredients on highest speed in a blender.
Pour into a large pie plate which has been well greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until set (a knife comes out clean).

title: stir-fried beef
directions: Combine stock, soy sauce, vinegar and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon of water.
In a large frying pan, heat 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add mushrooms and cook about 3 minutes. Stir in snow peas and cook 1 minute.
Remove vegetables and any liquid.
Heat remaining oil; add meat and sear about 3 minutes. Stir in garlic, ginger and stock mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch.
Cook briefly to thicken.
Stir in mushrooms, snow peas, scallions and water chestnuts and serve.

title: chocolate fondue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in pot.
Warm in medium saucepan.

title: candy bar angel cake
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on package for angel food cake. Remove from pan. Split cake horizontally to make 2 layers. (To split, mark side of cake with toothpicks and cut with long, serrated knife.)

title: blonde brownies or congo bars
directions: Blend the butter, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: tuna-asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place a small amount of soup over asparagus.
Place sliced eggs on top of soup.
Spoon tuna evenly over eggs; add remainder of soup.
Cover top with grated cheese or crushed potato chips.
Bake uncovered at 325° for about 20 minutes or until mixture is bubbly and top has browned.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Mix pecans and coconut and spread in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box. Pour over pecan mixture. Mix together the margarine, vanilla and cream cheese; spoon over the cake dough in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Best served warm.

title: curried green beans and potatoes
directions: Place potato slices in a medium saucepan.
Cover with water; bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Cover; cook for 5 minutes. Add green beans; cook, uncovered, for 8 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender.
Drain; set aside.
Combine curry powder and the next 4 ingredients in a large nonstick skillet; cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in yogurt and garlic; cook until mixture is warm.
(Do not overcook, or yogurt will separate.) Combine potato mixture and yogurt mixture in a large bowl; toss gently.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Yields 6 servings (serving size: 1 cup).

title: popcorn ribbon of fudge bars
directions: In large Dutch oven, over low heat, melt marshmallows with butterscotch chips and butter; stir occasionally until smooth. Add popcorn; toss until well coated.
Press 1/2 of mixture firmly into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread fudge sauce evenly over mixture.
Press remaining popcorn mixture over fudge.
Allow mixture to cool and harden.
Slide spatula under entire mixture and slice onto a cutting board to cut into bars.
Makes 16 bars.

title: butterscotch tassies
directions: Cream butter and cheese together.
Mix in flour a little at a time, creaming after each addition.
Chill about 3 hours.
Break off pieces the size of walnuts (depending on size of muffin pan) and with fingers, pat dough to cover bottom and sides of each lightly greased muffin cup.

title: kid chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Put cereal in a large bowl and pour melted ingredients over the cereal.
Stir to coat well.
Put half of the powdered sugar in a brown grocery bag. Add cereal mixture, then the rest of the powdered sugar.
Close bag and shake well to coat.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: soup-er teacher
directions: Take one teacher fresh from home.
Add above ingredients.
Put into morning classes until thoroughly shaken, approximately four hours.
Then place in teacher's lounge; add one cup of coffee.
Let simmer for half an hour.
Then add a heaping cup of courage and send back into afternoon classes, until teacher comes to a full boil.
Serves approximately 25 to 30 students.
Send leftovers (if any) home!

title: easy biscuits
directions: Place flour in bowl.
Stir in whipping cream until you have dough.
Sprinkle enough flour so dough isn't sticky.
Pat out biscuits with hands.
Place on greased and floured cookie sheet or pan.
Bake at 425° for about 40 minutes.
Makes 8 big biscuits or about 12 small.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in covered container up to 6 months.
Use 1/3 cup mix to cup of hot water.

title: cape cod cooler
directions: Fill tall glass with lemon-lime soda and cranberry juice. Serve over ice with lemon twist.

title: quick peach pie
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine and place in bottom of pan.
Add flour mixture, then the peach mixture.
Peel peaches.
Add sugar; let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream vegetable oil, butter and both sugars. Add vanilla and eggs. Sift dry ingredients. Stir in and blend. Roll a teaspoon of soft dough into a ball. Roll ball in granulated sugar. Press down on lightly greased cookie sheet with a glass tumbler dipped in sugar. Press dough with a fork to make a design. Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes. Makes about 8 dozen.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake and pudding mixes, eggs, water, oil and sugar, reserving 1 cup batter.
Pour nuts and chocolate bits into bottom of greased Bundt or tube pan, flat bottom.
Pour Hershey's syrup into reserved batter; mix well. Pour big batch of batter in pan, then pour syrup and batter mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour; cool for 20 minutes.
Remove from the pan.

title: chili chicken
directions: In large skillet, saute chicken in oil until no longer pink; set aside.
In same skillet, cook onion, pepper and garlic until tender; drain.
Stir in chili and stewed tomatoes.
Add rice; arrange chicken on top of mixture and top with shredded cheese. Simmer 10 minutes.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Stir or mix with mixer all ingredients.
Good on all raw vegetables and baked potatoes.

title: cheese and potatoes
directions: Put hash browns in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat cheese and mayonnaise until the cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes, mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Grease 13 in. x 9-inch dish.
Arrange potatoes; add onion. Crumble bacon over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with sliced butter.
Salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Blend butter and cheese.
Add flour and seasonings.
Press dough flat on lightly floured surface. Cut into rounds with biscuit cutter.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 24 biscuits.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash and sort dried beans. Put to boil, covered with water. Add baking soda.
Cover and allow to stand in water at least 1 hour or overnight, then drain and rinse well.
Add remaining ingredients and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook at medium heat until beans are tender (can mash easy with fork). Serve over cooked rice.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with coarsely chopped pecans.
Roll thawed bread dough into walnut-sized pieces.
Fill the pan with a single layer.
Heat other ingredients and pour over dough.
(Do not use microwave.)
Let rise in refrigerator overnight, covered.
Leave pan set out 1/2 hour before baking. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert to serve.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Beat egg with a fork; add oil and juice.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Frost with lemon icing.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef, onions and garlic.
Drain.
Mix with other ingredients and simmer at least 1 hour.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Dissolve sugar in 6 cups boiling water.
Mix with lime mixture.
Let cool and chill.
Mix remaining ingredients (except ginger ale) and keep cool.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, pork, onion and garlic in Dutch oven until meat is brown and onions tender.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato and break up with fork.
Stir in tomato sauce, 1/4 cup parsley flakes, sugar, 2 teaspoons salt and basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered about 1 hour or until mixture is like spaghetti sauce.

title: aunt tommie's pecan pie
directions: "When our blackberry bushes at the Westwood Circle house in Decatur were full of berries, our boys, Alan and Mark, would start begging Granny Bertha Brooks Austin to come to our house to cook a Juice Pie.
Vernon and the boys didn't like the seeds in the berries so Bertha would put water on the berries, bring to boil, strain the juice and make a cobbler.
I always had to call her for the recipe so this may not be exactly right."

title: honey dressing for fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar with tight-fitting lid.
Shake vigorously until thoroughly blended and chill before serving. Yield: about 1 1/2 cups.

title: butterscotch no-bake bars
directions: Mix together crackers, walnuts, coconut and marshmallows in large bowl.
In double boiler, or heavy saucepan, cook eggs, sugar and butter until it bubbles.
Cool until almost cold, then mix with graham cracker mixture.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or micro on Medium 5 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix as directed on the box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is baking, boil pineapple and sugar 5 minutes.
Pour over cake as soon as it comes out of the oven. Poke holes on top.
Let cool.
Prepare instant pudding as directed and spread over cooled cake.
Spread 8 ounces Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, cheese, onion and bacon bits.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour over broccoli. Mix well.
Marinate 8 hours before serving for best flavor.

title: quick healthy burritos
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
If desired, add 2 tablespoons organic salsa to this mixture.
Place mixture in the center of tortilla and fold.
Next, place all burritos on a microwave-safe dish and cook on High for 1 minute, uncovered.

title: apple enchiladas
directions: Cut each apple into 8 wedges.
Wrap each wedge with crescent roll.
Bake until done.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Stir all ingredients together and mix well. Put in a tightly closed jar. Use 3 tablespoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes.
Blend all ingredients together and beat for about 2 minutes, until potatoes are creamy.
Pour into pie crust and cook at 400° until medium brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: steamed brown bread
directions: Grease four 16-ounce vegetable cans (4 1/4 x 3-inch) or 7-inch tube mold.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, until blended. Fill cans about 2/3 full.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.

title: skillet cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat in egg.
Add brown sugar, flour, baking powder, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased 8-inch skillet.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: rice cereal pie crust(diabetic)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Line bottom and sides of 8-inch cake pan.
Chill well before adding fillings.

title: french baked chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in 1/2 stick butter. Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt. Pour small carton of whipping cream over browned chicken.
Cover with foil.
Cook in oven until done (30 to 45 minutes) at 350°.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: fireman's apple pie
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
Mix until crumbly.
Press in 2 greased 8-inch pie tins.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and melted oleo.
Place in the bottom of oblong pan.
Mix sugar, oleo, vanilla and eggs and beat for 15 minutes at high speed.
Be sure and beat for 15 minutes.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Slice bananas and arrange on cake.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas; top with Cool Whip.
Put nuts and cherries on top.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: see-kum-chee kook(korean spinach soup)
directions: Mix beef, onions, garlic, sesame seed, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Saute in bottom of heavy pan with a little oil until meat is seared.
Add water; cook until meat is tender.
Add spinach and cook until tender.
Serves 6.

title: wafer thins
directions: In mixing bowl, combine butter and cheese with a fork, then blend in flour and pepper by hand.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place on buttered 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking pan and flatten with heel of your hand until balls are about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake in preheated 350° oven uncovered for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown and crisp.
Cool on rack.
Makes 12 wafers.

title: johnny cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Cover 9 x 13-inch rectangular dish with graham crackers. Combine pudding mix with milk.
Mix pudding and whipped topping. Pour half of the mixture on crackers.
Place another layer of crackers.
Pour in the rest of the mixture.
Place a layer of crackers on the top.
Microwave icing slightly, so to soften. Pour icing over crackers and spread evenly.
Refrigerate.

title: apple julep
directions: Chill juices.
Combine first 4 ingredients with ice cubes; mix well.
Garnish servings with mint if desired.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Saute in skillet until crisp. Remove bacon and pour out all but 2 tablespoons of bacon fat. Saute onion in bacon fat for 3 to 4 minutes until soft.

title: pecan pie(makes 2)
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs, well beaten and blend well.
Add syrups, pecans and salt. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then lower to 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: cheese straws 2
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put through cookie press.
Bake at 300° until slightly brown.

title: marinated onions
directions: Mix all together and let sit overnight.

title: speedy chili
directions: Cook onion, peppers and beef together in a pan until the meat is lightly browned.
Then add tomato sauce; cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Add the kidney beans and salt.
Heat.
Stir in chili powder, taste.
Add a little more if you like.

title: angie's favorite potatoes
directions: Mix Potato Buds according to directions on box.
Add sour cream, cream cheese and garlic powder.
Pour into greased baking bowl and place pats of butter or margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until golden brown on edges.

title: one-step brownies
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix for 4 minutes (margarine should be softened).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake for 25 to 35 minutes, until done.
Do not overbake.
While hot, spread chocolate chips on top.
Let melt and spread like frosting.
Put back in oven (1 minute) if too hard to spread chocolate chips.

title: spudnuts
directions: To 1 pint warm water, add the dry yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix yeast mixture and all other ingredients, except flour and eggs.
Beat in the eggs, then mix in flour.
Do not knead! Roll, cut and deep fry.
Glaze.

title: asparagus luncheon platter
directions: Cook asparagus in boiling salted water 10 minutes. Mix mushroom soup, cream, lemon juice and egg yolk; season. Heat thoroughly. Pour over drained asparagus arranged on toast. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken almond rice
directions: Saute pork (pour off fat), onions, green pepper and celery for 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on top of stove for 5 minutes (large pan).
Pour into two casseroles and bake at 350° for one hour or until rice is soft and all liquid is absorbed.
Serves 20.
A great crowd pleaser!

title: butterscotch pull-apart rolls
directions: Place frozen rolls in a greased Bundt pan. Mix sugar, pudding mix and nuts; pour over rolls. Add the melted margarine. Let rise overnight and next morning, bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt butter and mix in flour; add milk until smooth.
Bring to boil until thickened.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread.
Let cool.
Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
In another pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter; add crab meat and warm.
Combine the two and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 450° until slightly brown, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: simple chocolate cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line muffin pans with foil cups.
Place 1 wafer in bottom of each.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, cocoa and flour; blend well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Fill each cup near full with mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.

title: corn and green chilies
directions: Drain corn.
Melt margarine and cream cheese.
Stir in corn, chives, sugar and chilies.
Spoon into a greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: one-step pasta casserole(microwave)
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, cook onion and garlic in oil, covered, on High for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.
Add beans with their liquid, tomato sauce, pasta, bouillon and 3/4 cup water.

title: apple pancakes
directions: In heavy 10-inch skillet, heat 2 tablespoons margarine. Add apples and cook over medium heat until tender.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat until light.
Mix salt and soda with flour and add alternately with juice.
Mix in fruit cocktail last and bake in moderate oven.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and water in heavy saucepan.
Cook over heat to hard ball stage.

title: aunt sally's cheese and macaroni
directions: Cover macaroni with water in a pot; bring to boil.
Cook until soft; drain.
In a large pot add macaroni, Velveeta cheese cut into cubes, sour cream, margarine, cream and water.
Simmer on low heat until thickens.
Remember it will thicken up even more as it cools down.
This is one of the most favorite recipes of the nieces and nephews.
She had to bring it to every family get-together.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat at medium for 3 minutes.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: In pan, melt butter, corn syrup and milk. Add sugar. Bring to boil. Reduce to medium. Cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla. Blend with mixer until smooth.

title: kansas corn
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Fold in crushed crackers.
Add beaten eggs and onion.
Season with salt and pepper; top with paprika.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1
hour.

title: crescent italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef, onion and mushrooms, drain. Add salt and pepper and tomato sauce.
Place in ungreased 8 x 12-inch dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Mix sour cream and herbs; spread one spoonful of the sour cream mixture on each triangle.
Roll up crescent roll starting at wide end.
Arrange on top of meat mixture and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: no bean chili dip
directions: Place in crock-pot and mix thoroughly.
Serve hot with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown round steak in margarine.
Push meat to side and stir flour into any meat drippings.
Add water and dry soup mix. Simmer 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and mushrooms in juice to form stroganoff gravy.
Serve over prepared egg noodles.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt butter, milk and caramels.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 cake pan.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 of cake mixture in cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Remove cake from oven and pour caramel mixture directly on top.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped nuts over caramel mixture.
Pour remaining half of cake mix over entire mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 250°.
Then turn oven up to 350° and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry gelatin cake
directions: Sift cake mix and gelatin together.
Add oil; add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in layer pans or bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour in
Bundt pan.

title: cheesy beef casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef with onions and green pepper.
Drain and discard fat.
Add green beans and tomato sauce; cook until warm.
In a greased 10-inch glass pie plate, pat enough biscuits together to form a bottom crust.
Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown.
Remove from oven and spoon ground beef mixture over crust.
Arrange shredded cheese over beef mixture.
Cut remaining biscuits in halves or quarters and roll in small balls. Arrange on top of cheese.
Return to 350° oven and bake until biscuits are golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: "salami"
directions: Knead all together.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Knead each day for 5 minutes.
Cover and replace in refrigerator.
On 4th day, knead and form in 5 rolls.
Bake 9 hours at 160°.
Bake in broiler pan so excess grease drops off.
Cool on paper towel.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine milk and bread and let soak, then add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in baking pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain, then add sauce and cook 10 minutes.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Did you ever get ready to have pancakes and find that your syrup is low?
Just make your own.
Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes.
(My mother used to make this.)

title: mom's nutmeg sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually stir in 2 cups boiling water.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in butter and nutmeg.
Keep hot until serving time.
Great on bread pudding, gingerbread or cottage pudding.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a bowl. Mix well and spread on one side of tortilla; roll up tightly. Wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Slice into 1-inch pieces. Serve with salsa or picante sauce. Yields about 5 dozen.

title: mother's cherry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in long glass casserole dish and add cherries. Mix remaining ingredients; pour over cherries.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Peach halves may be used instead of cherries and are good with nutmeg and cinnamon sprinkled on top.
Crust rises to the top.

title: no flop dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar with a fork.
(If using vanilla pudding, can add 2 cups of coconut.)
Spread on cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir last 15 minutes.
Cool. Put 2/3 in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix together hamburger, noodles, sauce, mushrooms and oregano in a big pan.
Spread Mozzarella cheese.
Place pepperoni on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix together and refill quart jar.
Mix will keep several months in refrigerator.

title: lettuce fruit salad
directions: Chop up lettuce; add cut up apples and bananas.
Cream mayonnaise and sugar together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Use about 1 teaspoon sugar to 3/4 cup of mayonnaise.

title: sauted pork chops and rice
directions: Season chops to taste. Don't be afraid to season; the more seasonings, the better flavor of the final dish.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add garlic and onion.
Brown lightly. Add water and cook 15 minutes, covered.
Mix cumin, salt, flour, pepper and chili powder.
Mix in cooked meat.
Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sundae
directions: Mix flour and oleo. Put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream the butter and confectioners sugar.
Add the flour about 2 cups at a time, mixing well.
Knead the mixture until all flour is mixed completely.
Place batter in a 3/4-inch deep pan and pat it out so it is 3/4 inch high.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ham dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Chop wafer ham, onions and water chestnuts.
Mix together. Form a ball. Eat with crackers.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage, carrots and smoked sausage.
Chop onion.
Cook in small amount of water (2 cups).
When vegetables are done cooking (steaming) add enough milk to cover all, then add 1/2 stick butter.
Season with salt and pepper to desired taste.
Mix flour with water in bowl to make thick mixture.
When mixture comes to a boil, thicken with flour and water to desired thickness (allow to cook for short period after every addition of flour and water, so mixture does not become too thick).
We enjoy this over toast on a cold winter day!

title: spinach filled pitas
directions: Thaw and squeeze out the spinach.
Combine chopped onion, onion soup mix, cream cheese and spinach.
Chop water chestnuts and add to spinach and cream cheese mixture.
Cut pitas in half; fill with the mixture.
Smooth out and cut halves into serving pieces.

title: banana fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add milk and water and then the egg to the dry ingredients and mix until batter is smooth. Peel bananas and slice lengthwise. Roll in flour, then dip in fritter batter, completely coating each piece. Fry in hot fat, turning fritters to brown evenly. Drain and serve hot.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and Hidden Valley Ranch. Set aside.
Press crescent rolls in bottom of cookie sheet and bake according
to package directions.
Cool.
Spread
cream cheese mixture on dough.
Sprinkle with your favorite veggies. Cut and serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Pour in medium size baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour into the butter.
Do not stir. Pour peaches and juice into baking dish.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: greek tortellini salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cooked pasta, sweet peppers, onion and olives.
For dressing, combine vinegar, oil, mint, lemon juice, sherry, seasoned salt, garlic powder, black pepper and red pepper. Pour over salad; toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill for 4 to 24 hours.
Stir in cheese.
Use a slotted spoon to serve.
Makes 12 to 14 side-dish servings.

title: joy's quiche
directions: Mix
eggs, well beaten, salt and pepper together.
Line a 9-inch
pie dish with prepared shell.
Sprinkle cheese, ham and whatever
else
desired
on bottom of pie shell.
Add egg mixture. Bake
at
425° for 15 minutes; set oven back to 325° and
bake for 40 minutes longer.
Done when knife inserted in middle comes out clean.	Serves 8.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and salt, then pecans.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Bake in oven at 325° for 20 minutes.
Do not brown.
Cool, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening with sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Last, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes (test).
Make 3 layers or one 9 x 13-inch pan (large cake).

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch together.
Add to undrained crushed pineapple.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear. Cool and set aside.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Spread cooled pineapple into unbaked pie shell.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 325° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Set in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Do not cover (makes it soggy).
Just before serving pour and stir sauce over broccoli. Mix together well.

title: velvet salad
directions: Heat pineapple and gelatin over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese and nuts.
Add pineapple mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into Pyrex dish and congeal overnight.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil macaroni; drain and set aside.
Chop celery, onion and eggs into small pieces and mix with macaroni.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries, adding 1 cup of sugar and allowing it to drain overnight.
Remove seeds from grapes.
Add whipping cream.
Mix all together.
Pecans improve flavor.
Marshmallows may be added for bulk.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and bone chicken.
Cook spaghetti and onion in chicken broth.
Drain spaghetti.
Add diced Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted.
Stir in chopped celery (not cooked), pimiento and soup, etc.
Put in dish and bake at 300° until light brown.
Serves 8 people.

title: no-bake oaties
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar, orange juice and orange rind.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Fold in oats and walnuts.
Chill 1 to 2 hours or until firm.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in shredded coconut.
Chill 1 to 2 hours or overnight.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs and oil.
Add mandarin oranges and juice.
Pour into sprayed cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, or until done.
Allow to cool before frosting.

title: honey muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl, pour milk over cereal and let stand for 2 minutes or until milk is absorbed. Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Pour in oil and honey and mix by hand.
Combine bran mixture and dry ingredients. Stir only until combined. Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: chunky garden salsa
directions: Blanch tomatoes; peel and core.
Cut into chunks.
Cook slowly over low heat.
Add small chunks of green or banana peppers, chopped onion, diced garlic and cut fresh and dried ground herbs and spices.
Add hot peppers to taste.

title: lemon things
directions: Mix cake mix (dry), 1/2 cup oleo and 1 egg. Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Mix together crackers, butter and sugar.
Press into bottom and sides of spring-form pan.
Combine Cool Whip, pudding and sour cream and mix with a wire whisk.

title: wassail
directions: Slowly bring all ingredients to a boil on the stove.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Best served hot.

title: quick herb rolls
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix in herbs and cheese. Cut biscuits into halves or fourths and swish around in herb-butter to coat all sides.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak Shredded Wheat in milk and combine with meats in which onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, tomato catsup and egg have been mixed.
Form into loaf and place in greased loaf pan.
Cut bacon strips in half and place on top of meat loaf.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rice pudding cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
After baking, top with whipped cream.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook onions for 10 minutes in boiling water. Lightly grease casserole. Layer 1/2 tomatoes, 1/2 onions and 1/2 cheese. Repeat. Sprinkle with melted butter, salt, pepper and basil. Cover with bread crumbs. Bake 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: asparagus beef stir-fry
directions: Preparation:
Cut asparagus into thin slices diagonally; slice flank steak very thin; mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup of water and seasonings; cut green onion for garnishing.

title: hot pizza sandwiches
directions: Preheat sandwich maker according to directions.
Spread sauce on 2 slices of bread, not all the way to edges.
Sprinkle pepperoni on sauce.
Add cheese.
Place slice of bread on top of each evenly.
Carefully place sandwiches in heated sandwich maker. Press to close, lock and leave 1 1/2 minutes or according to directions on appliance.
Open carefully and remove sandwiches very carefully.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix in hot water the gelatin which has been soaked in the cold water. Add to the vegetables and congeal.

title: scallop oysters
directions: Butter baking dish.
Put 1/2 inch crackers in dish.
Put in oysters; add salt and pepper and pats of butter. Put in 2 cups of cream.
Add more crackers about another 1/2 inch.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy honey sauce for baked chicken
directions: Use equal amounts of honey, melted butter and lemon juice. Heat on low just until blended.
This should be used during the last hour of baking of chicken.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix with a mixer.
Chill and serve.

title: chops in beer
directions: Brown chops.
Cover with catsup, beer and brown sugar.
Cook at low heat for 1 hour.

title: cashew pea salad
directions: Thaw frozen peas under running water. Drain & combine next five ingredients. Mix sour cream and ranch dressing. Pour over pea mixture; toss gently. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: 30 minute supper
directions: Saute onion and jalapenos in oil. Add meat after browning. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, black pepper, chili powder and red pepper. Cover.

Cook on medium heat. When meat has cooked 10 to 15 minutes, add corn. Cook over medium heat 5 to 10 minutes, covered. Serve over elbow macaroni, rice or boiled diced potatoes. Serves 3 to 5 depending how much rice you use.
If red pepper and jalapenos are both used, it may be warmish!

title: squirrel stew
directions: Cut up 3 squirrels in convenient-size pieces and place them in a large kettle; add 3 quarts of water. Bring to a boil slowly and simmer until the meat is tender (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours) or cook in a pressure cooker 30 to 45 minutes, depending on age of squirrel. REMOVE THE MEAT FROM THE BONES and put back in the water. Add bacon, cayenne, black pepper, salt, onion, tomatoes, tomato paste, potatoes and frozen vegetables. Cook for 1 hour. Then add corn and cook for another 10 minutes. Serve with corn bread. Serves 6.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Combine bouillon, soy sauce, sugar and sherry in bowl.
Add 1/2 mixture to meat.
Push meat to one side of frying pan.
Add onions and celery and cook over low heat 3 minutes.
Add remaining bouillon mixture, bamboo shoots, mushrooms, water chestnuts and cooked spinach.
Cook for three minutes.
Add green onions.
Cook 1 hour over low heat.
Serve over the cooked vermicelli.

title: tater-tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; drain off fat.
Place in bottom of a well-greased 2-quart baking dish, top with undiluted cream of mushroom soup, then top with cheese.
Finally cover with rows of Tater Tots; bake in oven at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts and Tots are golden brown.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Whisk all ingredients (except vegetables) in a deep bowl until well combined.
Add vegetables.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator 4 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry sherbet punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Add about 1 quart of water after all is thawed.
Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cake will crack slightly on top.
Cool in pan for 1 hour before removing.
Can be iced with cream cheese frosting, if desired.

title: sloppier joes
directions: Brown the hamburger until it is all broken apart.

Add the diced onion and cook until it is glazed. Add the tomatoes and simmer for 25 minutes without a cover. Stir from time to time to prevent scorching. Remove from heat and place a heaping spoonful of the meat mixture on the bottom of each hamburger bun (set aside the tops temporarily).
Sprinkle with the crisp bacon, then top with the grated cheese.
Place under the broiler until the cheese is melted.
Cover with bun tops and serve.

title: beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place Brisket in heavy foil pan. Mix other ingredients and pour over top.
Seal foil.
Bake 3 hours. Enjoy!

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Grease and flour 2 pie pans well.
Mix all the ingredients well; pour into the pie pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream the oil, sugar and eggs. Add buttermilk, soda, salt and vanilla alternately with the flour.
Beat well and add mashed bananas. Blend well.
Put into a greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes(100 years old)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients except flour.
Work in as little flour as possible, approximately 3 1/2 cups.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Put the margarine, water and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil.
In a bowl, put the sugar, flour and salt.
In another bowl, beat the eggs, sour cream, soda and vanilla.
Mix all 3 together. Bake on a cookie sheet for 20 minutes in a 400° oven and ice while hot.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook onion and celery in 1/2 cup oleo.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Heat together on low heat so it will mix well.
Add broccoli; mix altogether.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish and cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hunting style quail
directions: Brown birds in hot oil.
Sprinkle onion, garlic, parsley and tomato on them.
Pour over white wine; add salt, pepper, mustard, bay leaf and rosemary.
Braise until meat is tender.
Meanwhile, chop mushrooms coarsely and saute with bacon in a small amount of oil.
When meat is nearly done, add bacon and chopped mushrooms. Thicken with a paste of flour and water, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: lemon icebox pie cake
directions: Bake cake as directions state in two 9-inch cake pans.
Let cool and split each layer.
Mix Eagle Brand with lemonade (not diluted).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread layer of icing between each layer and then ice the sides.
Pretty and good.
(Tastes like lemon icebox pie.)

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Roll dough 1/4-inch thick; cut small, round cookies.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
(Take out just as edges begin to brown.)
I roll into log, refrigerate, cut thin and bake.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, bottom and top.

title: bland's vegetable sandwiches
directions: Room temperature for spreading.
Cut off edges of bread.

title: "quick and easy cherry fluff"
directions: Blend all ingredients together and chill.

title: wanda's vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar, salt and vanilla in bowl and mix thoroughly with mixer.
Pour into can; add condensed milk and stir well.
Add dairy milk to fill line on can and stir.
Makes 4 quarts.
If fruit is desired, add approximately 1 quart, then add milk to fill line on can.

title: moist apple loaf
directions: Mix apples, sugar and nuts together; let stand for 1 hour. Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and soda together; add to apple mixture alternately with oil, vanilla and eggs.
Pour batter into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Wrap in aluminum foil to keep moist.
Very good!

title: dumplings
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk and melted shortening and mix well.
Pour into self-rising flour and mix until just dampened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto meat or chicken which is barely covered with liquid. Cover tightly and boil gently, 10 to 14 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Measure all ingredients into a pan and heat to boiling.
Keep hot for basting.
This is enough for 3 chickens.

title: homemade pizza crust
directions: Mix in order given.
Spread on oiled pan that has been sprinkled with corn meal.
(This makes bottom crispy.)

title: chunky chicken rice soup
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Add water and the rest of the ingredients.
Cook until done.

title: sauce bordelaise
directions: Peel and chop shallots and place in saucepan.
Add red wine, thyme, bay leaf and salt.
Bring to a boil and reduce by half. Meanwhile, melt 1 tablespoon of butter in another saucepan.
Add flour; cook, stirring, until roux has browned.
Add stock, salt and pepper to taste, stirring well.
Cook over a low heat for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Dice the marrow and poach for 5 minutes in boiling water, then drain.
Remove the thyme and bay leaf from the wine reduction.
Add the marrow cubes, adjust the seasoning and leave to simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add meat juice. Remove from heat and add remainder of butter and chopped parsley, stirring continuously.

title: nutty o's
directions: Butter a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Heat brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and nuts; mix until well coated.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen with metal spatula.
Let stand about 1 hour.
Store in a covered container.

title: pork pies
directions: Place all ingredients, except potatoes, in large pan.
Cook on medium heat until meat is done.
Boil potatoes in salted water, then drain.
When meat is cooked, add potatoes and mash together.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze out water.
Combine; refrigerate at least 2 hours (overnight is best).
Serve in loaf of "King Hawaiian" bread.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Allow to cool.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread over crust.
Chill.
Combine pudding and milk.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spread over cheese layer and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: solyanka(a russian fish soup with capers and onions)
directions: In a large soup pot, heat the wine.
Add the onion and cook until softened.
Add the celery, carrots and the tomatoes and continue to cook for 5 minutes.
Peel, seed and slice the cucumber (about 1 1/2 cups); cut the fish in large chunks.
Add both to the soup and cook 3 minutes longer.
Add the water; bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer until the fish flakes easily (about 10 minutes).
Turn off the heat.
Add remaining ingredients and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: soap balls (not eatable)
directions: *Add any of these ingredients to equal 1/4 cup:
food coloring, flavoring for scent and water.
Mix this and Ivory Snow.
Shape into balls.
Makes 3 large balls.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 12-cup muffin tin or 3 miniature muffin tins (12 each) with vegetable cooking spray or grease lightly.
(Paper liners won't need oil.) Beat egg, oil and milk.
Stir in bananas.
Mix dry ingredients together and stir into banana mixture until flour is moistened.
Fill tins 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake about 23 minutes (15 to 18 minutes for small muffins).
Let cool about 15 minutes before removing from pans to let texture firm up.

title: brown rice
directions: In the order the ingredients are listed place them in a 9 x 9-inch dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: great mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased lightly, at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 14.

title: rebel's delight
directions: Mix in pan.
Season to taste with butter, salt and pepper and heat.
Field peas can be substituted but do not use black-eyed peas.
They don't have much taste.
If you like succotash, you'll love this simple but tasty dish.
It gets its name from "goober peas" which were the staple of the Confederate Army.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix the beef, bread crumbs, milk and onion thoroughly.
Shape into bite size balls.
Brown in margarine all around.
Pour off the fat.
Mix the wine, catsup, oregano and paprika.
Pour over the meatballs in the skillet.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Keep checking so they don't burn.
Serve spiked with toothpicks.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt together in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and with fork, lightly beat eggs into pumpkin mixture.
Add the milk and evaporated milk. Mix well.
Place in 9-inch pie plate and bake at 375° for 25 minutes with edges of pie covered with foil.
Remove foil and bake for 25 more minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean. Cool and chill to serve.

title: barbecued ribs(5 to 8 servings)
directions: In large pan with cover, cook ribs in boiling water 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
In medium saucepan, combine remaining ingredients; simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove ribs to grill.
Turn often and brush with sauce.
Chicken may be used instead of ribs.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Drain pineapple reserving juice.
Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add Mountain Dew and pineapple juice.
Cool.
Add crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
When firm, spread pie filling on top. Spread Cool Whip on top of pie filling.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger with 1/2 package of taco seasoning; drain. Warm refried beans and mix with remaining package of taco seasoning.
In your casserole dish, bottom layer of refried beans. Next, layer hamburger.
Then add sour cream and next salsa.
Final step, shredded cheese on top.
Put in oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve warm with chips.

title: banana pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, gradually blend milk and pudding mix.
Add egg yolks and 1 teaspoon vanilla, beating until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until pudding comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover with plastic wrap and cool thoroughly, about 30 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream to which remaining vanilla had been added.
Arrange 1/2 ladyfingers in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole baking dish.
Spoon 1/2 pudding over cake and 1/2 bananas over pudding; repeat layers again.

title: connie's cornbread casserole
directions: Pour 1/2 of cornbread mix in casserole.
Add sausage and cheese; do not mix.
Pour rest of mix over top.
Bake at 325° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes in foil
directions: Slice potatoes into a large piece of foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Crumble bacon over potatoes.
Add onion and cheese. Dot with butter.
Wrap loosely and seal well with double fold. Cook in 350° oven for about 1 hour or until done, turning occasionally.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: imperial crab
directions: In saucepan, melt 1 tablespoon butter; mix flour.
Gradually add milk until it comes to a boil and thickens.
Mix onion and Worcestershire sauce and bread and cool.
Fold in mayonnaise, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter until brown; add crabmeat and mix all together.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Line baking dish with pie crust.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 cup flour together.
Put 1/2 of this mixture into pan (over the crust). Mix remaining sugar and flour mixture into the blackberries.
Add this onto the crust and sugar layer.
Add the remaining 2 cups sugar on berries.
Add enough water to cover the berries.
Top with crust.
Sprinkle top with a little sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is brown and berries are done.

title: medallion of pork(with mushroom sauce)
directions: Cut pork into 1/8 inch thick medallions.
Heat 1 tsp. oil in a large skillet.
Add medallions and saute over high heat until they are golden brown on both sides.

title: block-party beans
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and catsup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: I make my dumplings and freeze at least overnight. They do not break up as easily.

title: squash casserole
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add other ingredients in order given (not nutmeg).
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into the mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole and sprinkle nutmeg on the top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting when mixture reaches a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until blended. Spoon onto wax paper or cookie sheet.

title: grandma annie's plain cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.
Serve with fruit and topping.
A great cake for serving with strawberries.
Serves 10.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions in margarine until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes on low, stirring occasionally.
Cool and store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: cornmeal pastry
directions: Measure flour, cornmeal and and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening thoroughly.
Sprinkle in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing until all flour is moistened.
Gather into a ball.
Roll into a rectangle, 12 x 8-inches, on lightly floured cloth covered board.
Fold lengthwise in half; cut slits in folded edge.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and soda together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add oats and nuts.
Mix together.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pepperoni soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine lentils, water, pepperoni, onion, tomato paste, salt, oregano, sage and cayenne.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato, carrots and celery; cover and simmer 40 minutes.

title: chicken a la easy
directions: Mix cheese and stuffing mix.
Dip chicken in oleo and then roll in mixture.
Bake at 350° in covered dish for 45 minutes. Remove top and cook an additional 15 minutes.

title: simple granola
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil and honey in large mixing bowl.
Mix oil and honey together; pour over oat mixture.
Mix well.
Spread into 2 (15 x 10 x 1-inch) baking pans.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 20 minutes, stirring once.
Remove from pan when cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: cake(easy and delicious)
directions: Prepare gingerbread according to directions on box.
Add some mincemeat.
Bake.
Frost with brown sugar and nut frosting.

title: chafing dish mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet at 250°.
Add mushrooms caps, round side up.
Sprinkle garlic salt over mushrooms until completely covered (additional garlic salt may be needed); add onions, cover, leaving vent open.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, depending on the size of the mushrooms.
Stir once.
Drain butter. Fold in sour cream and sprinkle with paprika.
(The butter can be used to saute the mushroom stems.)

title: hearty manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cook sausage 5 minutes in 1/4 cup water until brown.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef with onion.
Stir in tomato paste and puree, salt, basil, sugar, pepper and water.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add sausage.
Cook another 15 minutes.
Boil shells according to pkg directions.
Drain.
Mix cheeses and parsley. Pour half of meat mixture into casserole pan.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture.
Place on top of meat mixture.
Cover with remaining meat mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
well.
Pour
into greased muffin tins and bake
in a preheated oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until brown.
Serve warm.
Yields 6 to 8 muffins.

title: minute steak and gravy
directions: Salt and pepper minute steaks.	Roll in flour.	Put in skillet with melted Crisco.
Brown on both sides.
Add 2 cups water over steaks.	Put lid on skillet and let simmer about 20 minutes.

title: chicken lasagna bake
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water, drain again, set aside.
Combine soup, broth, stir until smooth; set soup mixture aside.
Combine cream cheese and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed with electric mixer 1 minute or until smooth.
Stir in onion and next 3 ingredients.
Set cream cheese mixture aside.
Layer half each of lasagna noodles, cream cheese mixture, chicken and soup mixture in a lightly greased 13x9x2-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Combine breadcrumbs and butter, sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. 12 servings.

title: impossible zucchini and tomato pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients well and pour into greased baking dish.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add enough buttermilk to make a thick
batter.
Bake in a 450° oven in a small greased pan until done.

title: hershey's chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs ONE-AT-A-TIME, beat well after each egg.
Add syrup and vanilla.
Beat add stir in flour. Bake in 9 X 13 pan that has been greased and floured in a 350 degree for 45 - 50 minutes.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioner sugar for garnish.

title: basic quaker oat bran muffins
directions: This is a low fat, low cholesterol recipe, adapted from Quaker Oat Bran recipe on its box, by a heart patient.
I've tried them and I think they are great.
There are other brands of oat bran on the market but I prefer the Quaker brand texture.
I don't like bran muffins too sweet so 2 tablespoons of sweetener is enough for me.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Tumble the beef pieces in a Dutch oven with the soup mix.
Add 1 cup of wine and place in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add soup after 1 hour; stir well.
It may be necessary to add water if in a "holding pattern."
Serve over hot pasta.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat with seasonings and drain.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Season again with soy sauce and Worcestershire.
Add color with Kitchen Bouquet.
Serve over macaroni or rice.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan the pretzels, butter and sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: vegetable slim dip
directions: Place milk and cottage cheese in blender container.
Process on high speed until smooth and creamy. Stir in soup mix. Refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: creamy basil fettucini
directions: Cook fettucini according to package directions.
Drain and immediately toss with oil, garlic and yogurt.
Add Parmesan cheese, basil, salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 serving.

title: lemon pudding pound cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add cake mix, pudding (dry), water and oil; beat at medium speed 10 minutes.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan with removable bottom.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Remove hot cake on bottom pan from pan.
Using a 2-tined fork, prick holes in top of cake.
Drizzle glaze over top and spread on sides of cake.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar until creamy. Add eggs and beat well. Mix dry ingredients. Add dry mix.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Cool and split layers. Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Reserve 1 cup of sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers of cake, split side up.

title: sausage, chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Saute onions and mushrooms in 2 tablespoon of butter or oleo.
Cook rice according to package directions.

title: soda cracker torte
directions: Beat eggs until stiff.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fill buttered 9-inch pie tin.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Cover top with apricot jam and whipped cream or soft ice cream.

title: quick cookies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add dry cake mix and eggs; mix. Fold in chocolate chips.
Mixture will be stiff.
Press into bars. Makes 48 bars.

title: banana pudding
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding as directed.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Place in the refrigerator.
Line pan with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding mixture. Pour half of the mixture over bananas and wafers.
Repeat.
May top with vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate 4 to 8 hours.

title: cinnamon 'n sugar muffins(makes 1 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat eggs in a large bowl until frothy.
Stir in milk, applesauce and 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in raisins, 1/4 cups sugar, baking powder, salt and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon all at once just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups (about 1/3 full).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Mix in
1/4 cup sugar and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Immediately dip tops of warm muffins into 1/4 cup melted butter, then into cinnamon mixture.

title: hi-protein honey wheat bread
directions: Heat water, honey, margarine and cottage cheese until 120°. Add 2 cups flour, eggs, salt, oats, nuts and yeast.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Knead dough on floured surface for 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Form 2 balls and let rest for 15 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in pans and cover; let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt chocolate, butterscotch and butter in double boiler.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread on buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate until set, 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery together, add chicken.
Mix chow mein noodles, milk and soups together.
Add to chicken mixture, pour all in large casserole dish.
Melt one stick butter and toss with stuffing mix or croutons.
Use this mixture as topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: three-cheese macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish (lightly greased), combine hot macaroni, soup, milk, seasonings, 1/4 cup each of the cheeses and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining Parmesan cheese, French fried onions, Cheddar and Swiss cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put coconut and nuts in bottom.
Mix chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix margarine, sugar and cream cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls over cake mix.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: evalene's christmas divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water in saucepan to boiling point; stir constantly.
Reduce heat and continue cooking until a few drops tested in cold water forms a hard ball at 250° on candy thermometer.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine flour, margarine, sugar and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.

title: chinese macaroni salad
directions: Simmer onion, green pepper and celery in oil until cooked. Add drained mushrooms.
Mix onion mixture and mushrooms to macaroni.
Add cooked chicken and soy sauce.
Serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Blend corn and beans; spread in bottom of rectangular Pyrex dish.
Mix next 4 ingredients together and spread over vegetables. Stir crackers into melted butter.
Sprinkle topping on top of other ingredients. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Bake at 400° until done.

title: hearty beef enchiladas
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook beef and onions over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in beans, 2 cans enchilada sauce and 1 cup salsa; set this aside. In a skillet, heat 1/4-inch of oil. Dip each tortilla in hot oil for 3 seconds on each side or just until limp. Drain on paper towels. Top each tortilla with 2/3 cup beef mixture; roll up and place seam side down in 4 (13 x 9 x 2) baking dishes. Drizzle with remaining enchilada sauce and salsa. Sprinkle with cheese and olives. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 28.

title: almond bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together margarine and almond paste; beat in sugar and eggs.
Add flour and salt; pour in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 40 minutes.
Cool and then cut.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Oven: 425°.
Add sugar and warm water to yeast.
Set in warm place.
Cut butter into flour.
Add yeast and enough milk to make soft dough.
Pat out on floured surface.
Melt butter in oven in 9-inch round pan.
Remove when melted, dip biscuits and turn over. Bake until golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Double for larger recipe.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water; stir until smooth. Cook for 5 minutes. Add beets to the hot sauce and let stand for 30 minutes. Just before serving, bring to a boil and add butter. Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Fry and crumble meat.
Drain and set aside.
Melt cheese. Add seasonings and meat.
Spread generously on slices of party rye.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly (about 10 minutes).
Can be made ahead and frozen unbaked.

title: cream cheese streusel brownies
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Cut margarine into 1/2 cup dry brownie mix until crumbly; stir in nuts and reserve.
Mix remaining dry brownie mix, 1 egg, oil and water.
Spread in pan. Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing on medium speed until well blended.
Add 1 egg and spread over brownie mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with reserved brownie mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: rice krispies candy
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and add last 3 ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: kisses
directions: Knead all together and roll into balls.
Roll into mixture of ground nuts and sugar.
Press in with thumb and fill with lekvar or jelly.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Boil 5 minutes in salted water until tender but not mushy.
Mix other ingredients and pour over warm carrots (after draining).
Stir well, then refrigerate.
Last up to one week in refrigerator.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Add green onions (tops too). Add bacon crumbles and raisins.
Make dressing with remaining ingredients and blend into salad.

title: low-fat double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch cake pan with nonstick spray.
In medium bowl using electric mixer on high speed, beat eggs until doubled in volume.
Slowly add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in liqueur.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients except chocolate chips.
Add to egg mixture, stirring and folding just until combined.
Pour into cake pan and bake for 20 minutes until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove to wire rack and cool.

title: miami beach birthday cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter; cool.
Stir in nuts and 2/3 cup chocolate chips; set aside.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water together.
Add strawberries with juice, pineapple, chopped pecans and sliced banana.
Pour half of mixture into
9 x 9-inch
dish.
Refrigerate 15 to 30 minutes until set.
Pour sour cream over chilled mixture.
Pour remaining strawberry mixture over sour cream.
Chill until firm.
Ready to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: persian chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken, if desired.
Mix all ingredients and add chicken.
Cover and marinate 24 to 48 hours.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, additional 1/2 hour uncovered.
Makes wonderful gravy.
Serve over rice.

title: thin 'n crispie sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs and flavorings; mix thoroughly. Stir dry ingredients together and blend in.
Refrigerate dough 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough and roll 3/16-inch thick on lightly floured pastry cloth.
Cut with cookie cutter; sprinkle with sugar.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes, or until golden.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Put together flour, soda, cream or tartar and salt and stir into shortening, sugar and eggs.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll each in mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake until lightly browned but still soft (cookies puff up at first, then flatten down) in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sauteed squash and tomatoes
directions: Wash squash well, scrubbing with a brush.
Slice into 1/2-inch thick diagonal slices.
In butter in medium skillet with tight fitting cover, saute onion, stirring, until golden, about 3 minutes.
Add squash and remaining ingredients; toss lightly to combine.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes, or until squash is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oven baked fudge pies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, salt and vanilla with a spoon.
In a separate bowl, melt oleo or butter and pour over the mixed dry ingredients. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well in between.
Add the can of Pet milk very slowly, mixing well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 400° for 10 minutes then reduce oven to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: First beat egg, add sour cream and buttermilk.
Mix the rest of ingredients together.
