Let stand 10 minutes before baking, batter swells.
Makes 10, 4 inch pancakes.
Yum!
Yum!

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Drain
juice from pickles.
Cut into quarters or rounds and put back into jar.
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices and pour over pickles.
Shake occasionally to get sugar to dissolve.

title: bean and beef burito
directions: Drain salsa and reserve liquid.
Brown ground beef.
Drain. Add seasoning mix, beans, chilies and liquid from salsa and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Spoon 1/3 cup mixture on a tortilla and top with 1 tablespoon each of salsa, lettuce and cheese.
Fold nearest edge of tortilla over to cover filling and fold in both sides envelope fashion and roll.

title: cranberry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, oats, 3/4 cup brown sugar and margarine.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press the rest into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sausage and beans
directions: Fry sausage, onion and celery; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Break taco shells in medium size pieces.
Cook beef and onion; drain.
Combine chilies, soup and tomatoes.
Add to meat with chili powder, salt and pepper.
Arrange 1/2 of taco shells on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon 1/2 of meat on top.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over meat.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry sparkle punch
directions: Puree strawberries in blender; dissolve gelatin in hot water. Stir in lemonade concentrate until melted; add cocktail and cold water and puree.
Pour over ice in punch bowl; slowly pour in ginger ale.
Makes about 30 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chicken dish
directions: Saute the onion, pepper and celery in 1 stick butter. Mix cubed bread, mayonnaise, eggs, chicken and milk, then add the sauteed mixture. Put in bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix well.
Put on buns under broiler until hot.

title: applesauce sweet potatoes
directions: Put sweet potatoes in a baking pan; sprinkle with salt.
Put applesauce on sweet potatoes.
Mix brown sugar, rolled oats and cinnamon.
Stir in margarine or butter.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 375° (moderate oven) about 45 minutes, until lightly brown.
Makes six servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and chocolate in saucepan over low heat.
When margarine and chocolate are melted, remove from heat.
Add in vanilla and eggs; mix in well.
Add flour and sugar; stir well.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly.

title: potato slices
directions: Scrub potatoes and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Put in cold water for 30 minutes.

title: lime pickles
directions: Combine first three ingredients and let stand for 24 hours. Rinse and pour off.
Rinse once each hour for four hours.

title: fried plantains(tostones de platanos - spanish recipe)
directions: Peel plantains and cut into diagonal slices, 1-inch thick.
Add salt to water.
Soak plantain slices for 15 minutes.
Drain well and deep fry in oil, heated to 350°, for about 7 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on absorbent paper.
Fold the paper over the slices and pound flat with the palm of the hand.
Deep fry in fat, heated to 375°, until crisp and golden.
Remove and drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Makes 12 to 18.

title: heavenly caramel apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, sour cream, eggs and vanilla on medium speed for 3 minutes. Mix dry ingredients, then add to sour cream mixture. Stir in apples and 1/3 cup pecans. Pour into greased loaf pan. Top with remaining pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool and remove from pan. Melt butter with brown sugar in saucepan and boil 1 minute. Drizzle on bread and serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: fruit punch
directions: Pour fresh boiling water over tea; steep for 5 minutes. Strain.
Add orange and lemon juices.
Chill thoroughly.
Add ginger ale and pour over ice in punch bowl.
Float orange slices and halved strawberries.

title: spinach dip i
directions: Mix well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken verona
directions: Mix bread crumbs with Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and mustard.
Mix melted butter with garlic.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter mixture, dredge in the crumb mixture and arrange in layers in pans.
Sprinkle remaining butter over chicken and bake 350 degrees for about 45 minutes to one hour.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Melt butter, then blend sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour.
Mix by hand.
If batter is too thick, add 2 tablespoons of milk.
Mix well and drop cookie mixture with a teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes or until done.

title: claudia's fantastic banana bread
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease
loaf pan.
Sift flour and measure; resift
flour with powder, soda and salt.	Set aside. Cream shortening and sugar in 3 quart mixing bowl until smooth and fluffy.
Add
eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Stir in freshly mashed bananas.
Add flour a little at a time and mix. Turn into prepared pan and bake for 50 minutes or until a cake tester inserted
into
bread
comes out clean.
Remove cake to rack to cool before slicing.

title: homestyle bean soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours).
Remove bones, bay leaf, peppercorns and celery sprigs before serving.
Taste for salt adjustment. Trim meat from ham bone and return cut-up pieces to soup.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine the ingredients in the order listed and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer or until filling is firm.

title: chile con queso dip
directions: Heat margarine or oil until hot.
Stir in flour.
Add vegetables and approximately 1 1/2 cups water, stirring until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Add cheese, cubed and picante sauce. Stir constantly until mixture returns to a simmer.
Turn heat down very low and simmer about 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: microwave chili cheese dogs
directions: Split buns partway through.
Spoon 1 tablespoon chili on each. Place frankfurters in buns.
Top each frankfurter with another tablespoon of chili and add 2 strips of cheese.
Arrange 4 paper napkins or paper towels on carousel.
Place filled buns on napkins, leaving an open center.
Microwave on Medium-high until filling is heated and cheese starts to melt (2 to 5 minutes).
If you do not have a carousel in your microwave, rearrange once or twice.

title: ground beef cornbread casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion over medium heat.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add chili powder, garlic salt and salt; mix well.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 can water and beans.
Spread over meat mixture.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Remove any cartilage from the crab meat and set the crab aside. In a thick pot, warm cream, sherry, chicken base and seasoning to slow simmer. In a separate pan, toast the roux (flour and butter) for a few minutes until it smells of toasted nuts (do not burn). Add roux to cream; bring back to a simmer and whisk until smooth. Serve garnished with the chopped parsley and pass a cruet of sherry. Serves 4 to 6.

title: bobby burger
directions: In large pot cook onion slightly in butter.
Add meat and cook.
Do not brown!
Mix chili sauce, mustard, onion, hot sauce, and chili powder.
Add mixture to meat and simmer for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve on hamburger buns or hot dog buns.

title: sugarless banana muffins(low calorie)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine vegetable oil, brown sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, Egg Beaters, oat bran, oatmeal and wheat germ.
Stir lightly with spoon to moisten.
Stir in banana.
Fill paper lined muffin tins or spray tins with nonstick vegetable spray.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out dry. Remove muffins from tins and cool on wire rack.
These muffins freeze well.
Yields 18 muffins.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: In a saucepan combine olive oil, butter and garlic.
Heat for 3 minutes.
Add clams.
In separate pot, cook linguine to preferred doneness.
Drain.
Place linguine in large bowl and pour clam sauce over it.
Add parsley to taste.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Remove from stove.
Mix eggs, sugar, milk, cottage cheese, pineapple and vanilla together. Pour melted butter over mixture.
Place noodles in casserole. Pour pudding mixture over noodles.
Press noodles into casserole bottom to cover with liquid.
Sprinkle crushed cornflakes on top (with a pinch of nutmeg and cinnamon).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook beef until brown, stirring to crumble; drain off excess grease. Spoon beef into 8-inch square baking dish. Top with pizza sauce and cheese. Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs; beat until smooth. Pour mix over casserole, covering evenly. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Let stand for a few minutes before cutting into squares for serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Good for all types of fruit.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers. Remove seeds and membranes. Precook pepper cups in boiling salted water about 5 minutes, then drain. Cook ground beef and onion until meat is lightly browned. Season with salt and pepper. Add tomatoes, water, rice and Worcestershire sauce. Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 15 minutes. Stir in American cheese. Stuff peppers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour.
Add salt, coconut and nuts.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in preheated 275° oven.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Spread Russian dressing on six slices of rye bread.
Divide corned beef evenly among slices, then the Swiss cheese.
Top each with about 2 tablespoons of sauerkraut.
Spread remaining bread slices with mustard, if desired, and put this slice, mustard side down, on sandwiches.
Lightly butter both sides of sandwiches and grill slowly on each side until browned and cheese is melted. Serve with dill pickles.

title: no milk rolls
directions: Cream the first 2 ingredients together.
Add as listed, using yeast water last; beat well.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Beat dough down.
Put into covered container.
Rolls will keep up to 2 weeks. Take dough out, knead and roll out rolls as you need them.
Let stand 1 hour, then bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: toffee coffee mix
directions: You will need a 1-quart wide-mouth jar.

title: honey banana muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2/3 cup almonds in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, banana, milk and oil. Add to dry mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased and floured muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.
Combine honey and butter, mixing well. Dip top of muffin in honey mixture
and sprinkle with almonds.
Yields 14 muffins.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper.
Add V-8 juice, tomatoes and water.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Add cabbage and continue cooking 1/2 hour.
Serve with crusted bread.

title: individual american pizzas
directions: Brown meat with seasonings.
Drain well.
When ready to serve, open 1 can biscuits, flatten out and place on greased baking sheet with 2 spoonfuls of meat on each one.
Top with cheese.
Place in 350° oven and bake until biscuits are done.
Serve while hot. Very good with a tossed salad.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar and salt in 1 1/4 cups boiling water. Add frozen strawberries.
When mixture starts to jell, fold in Cool Whip.
Crumble angel food cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour strawberry mixture over cake.
When set, cut into squares.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Roll chicken in flour mix.
Place in pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn.
Bake for 10 more minutes.
Mix soup and 1 cup buttermilk.
Pour mix over chicken.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Continue to bake until chicken is tender.

title: steak bake
directions: Place meat in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Toss to coat meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper, tomatoes, mushrooms, molasses and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir in beans.

title: baked spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown onion, green pepper, celery and ground beef.
Put Ragu sauce, catsup, salt, pepper, garlic powder and oregano into the beef mixture.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.
Grease baking dish.
Put a layer of cooked spaghetti in dish; add 1/2 of spaghetti sauce on spaghetti, then repeat layers until all is used.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple; add water to make at least 2 cups. Heat to boiling; add eggs, sugar, cornstarch and salt which have been beaten together.
Cook until thick; remove from heat and add marshmallows.
When dissolved, add pineapple and vanilla; cool, then add Cool Whip and nuts.

title: blueberry oat muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Stir until moist.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin pans sprayed with Pam. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
In mixer, cream the sugar, butter and cream cheese; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each egg at low speed.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan or an iron skillet.
Place in a cold oven; bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle nuts in bottom of well-greased 10-inch round Bundt pan.
Set aside.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; boil 5 minutes.
Add nuts and boil 5 minutes.
Add soda and stir well.
Pour in buttered pan.
Cut in squares.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Add flour. Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: oriental rice
directions: Cut up green onions.
Fry in oil, stirring constantly, approximately 10 minutes.
Then stir in eggs until done.
Add mushrooms and soy sauce; cook 4 minutes.
Add rice and mix.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Add in marshmallows (melt), stir until creamed.
Add in Rice Krispies and stir.
Pour into dish and let set and cool.
When completely cool, cut into squares for serving.

title: patable pie crust
directions: Spray a 9-inch glass pie plate with nonstick coating; set aside.
Combine flour, oil and salt in mixing bowl.
Add water and stir to form ball.
Place dough in prepared pan and use fingers to pat onto bottom and sides.
Flute edges.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Whip Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in lemonade, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Fold all ingredients together.
Spoon into pie crust. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken 'n broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of flat bakeware.
Add cooked and boned chicken.
Mix soup, broth and mayonnaise.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Cover with generous amount of Cheddar cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs which have been tossed in melted oleo.
Bake at 375° until crackers are browned.

title: vegetable dip (amish)
directions: Mix until smooth and creamy.
Serve with crackers, cauliflower, celery, chips, whatever.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place frozen broccoli in microwave-safe casserole dish. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover; microwave on High for 10 minutes. Stir after 5 minutes. Stir in soup, then sprinkle cheese over broccoli. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
tags: cream of broccoli with cheese soup

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Place in layers on bread, cheese, kraut and beef.
Toast.

title: world's greatest cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Gradually add the white and brown sugars.
Cream until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until smooth.
Sift flour, measure and then sift again with soda into the mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Then slightly flatten cookie dough with the back of spoon. Bake in moderately slow oven at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Pour into casserole.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: coffee cake
directions: Measure 2/3 cup of cake mix.
Cut butter until crumbly.
Mix sugar and nuts.
Set aside.
Beat eggs lightly with fork.
Add sour cream to eggs and rest of cake mix and beat.
Batter will be thick and slightly lumpy.
Pour 1/2 the batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of topping with nuts. Repeat in 2 layers.
Top with rest of topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Check after 30 minutes.
Cake will pull away from sides when done.

title: tennessee hoe cakes
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Shape with hands into oblong cakes.
Bake on a well-greased griddle, turning when partly done so both sides will brown.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo to a boil for 1 minute.
Add oats, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: fruit punch
directions: Make syrup by combining sugar and water.
Heat to boiling. Cool.
Combine fruit juices.
Add cooled sugar syrup.
Chill. Just before serving, add ginger ale.
If desired, add food coloring of your choice.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Mix together in a double boiler and cool.
Serve with crackers.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water. Makes about 48 cups hot chocolate.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt together.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain. Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add drained cucumbers and onions.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Jar and seal.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine margarine, buttermilk and cocoa in saucepan.
Stir until it begins to boil and thicken.
Add vanilla, nuts and sugar. Beat until thick.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and 1/2 cup sugar together 4 times.
Mix egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and flavorings with beater until soft peaks form.
Add the remaining sugar in 4 additions; fold the flour mixture into the egg whites.
Turn into an angel food cake pan and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain; add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Put in 8-inch dish. Put cheese into strips and place on top of meat.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or an 8-inch square baking pan.
In a large bowl, mix together cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.

title: hawaiian style barbecued chicken
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in all of the ingredients up to pineapple chunks.
Cover and bake at 300° for an hour until done. During the last 15 minutes, add the pineapple chunks, oranges and almonds and continue to bake.
Serve with rice.

title: spicy walnuts
directions: Heat walnuts halves in moderate oven (375°) 5 minutes, stirring once.
Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In saucepan combine sugar, water, cinnamon and salt.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook without stirring to soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat.
Beat by hand one minute or until the mixture begins to get creamy.
Add vanilla and warm walnuts.
Stir until coated.
Turn mixture out onto buttered platter.
Separate at once, using two forks.
Yields 1 pound.

title: special cake
directions: Bake the cake mix in sheet cake pan as directed on box.
Mix the pineapple with the sugar; bring to a boil (5 minutes); pour over cake while still hot.
Let cool.
Mix the pudding as directed on box.
Add sour cream.
Spread on cool cake.
Top with Cool Whip after entire cake has cooled.
Keep in cool place.

title: overnight cabbage slaw
directions: Mix and let stand while preparing vegetables.

title: "pink stuff"
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Cool Whip.
Fold in the Cool Whip and chill.
Serves 8 to 10 or more.

title: chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings in a single layer in a large baking dish. Combine all other ingredients, excluding the sesame seed, in a bowl and stir until sugar dissolves.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Lightly grease Pyrex pie dish.
Slice jalapenos into bottom of dish; add onion.
Spread cheese over peppers and onions.
Salt eggs; beat well and pour over other ingredients.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: meat loaf pizza
directions: In skillet brown onions and pepper.
In bowl season meat with Season-all, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix together onion and pepper with meat mixture.
Pat meat mixture gently into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, drain off excess fat with spoon.
Spread on sauce, cheese and oregano.
Bake for 10 minutes. You may add the chopped onions and green peppers with the cheese mixture instead of the meat mixture.
Serves 4.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Bring to boil vinegar, water, sugar and pickling spice.
Add other ingredients and heat until cucumbers change color.

title: turkey fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together lightly.
Chill and serve.

title: banana cake supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Put all ingredients in bowl. Mix until smooth.
Bake for 1 hour in an angel food pan or Bundt.
A large tube pan is best.
Let cool 5 minutes before turning onto wire rack.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well so oil doesn't separate.
Add flour mixed with cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir in cereals, oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cookies are slightly browned.

title: never fail corn pudding
directions: Combine butter, eggs, milk, flour, sugar and salt.
Beat with wire whisk.
Add corn and whisk again.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream together and pour half the batter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour remaining cake batter over the sugar and cinnamon.
With knife cut through cake in a swirling motion.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Poke holes in cake while hot and pour topping over cake.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add shredded cheese and blend with butter.
Sift flour and add salt and paprika.
Add dry ingredients into cheese mixture.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
(These can be frozen until ready to bake.)
Place on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Balls will be puffed and brown.

title: good & spicy meatballs & sauce
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Crush cornflakes, add remaining ingredients and shape into little balls. Bake on cookie sheet 12 minutes or until brown. Place on paper towels while making sauce.

title: fiesta cornbread salad
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix and set aside.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and add little juice from pineapple if needed.
(Do not add milk to pudding.)

title: snowy coconut cottage ring
directions: In a small pan sprinkle gelatin over water to soften.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Cool.
In a large bowl, combine cottage cheese, sweetened condensed milk and coconut. Stir in cooled gelatin and mix well.
Turn into lightly oiled 1 1/2 quart ring mold.
Chill 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold onto lettuce leaves and fill center with fruit or melon.

title: lemon-dill steamed carrots
directions: Arrange carrots in a steamer basket; place over boiling water. Cover and steam 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Transfer carrots to a serving dish; keep warm.
Combine cornstarch, water and lemon juice in a small saucepan, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add dill and remaining ingredients, stirring until margarine melts.
Toss with carrots.

title: wedding cake frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour until it thickens, stirring constantly. Use egg beater if it lumps.
Cool.
Gradually beat in remaining ingredients into cooled flour sauce.
Frosts 3 layers.

title: pam's garden special
directions: Cook for 20 minutes; freeze or can.

title: pineapple crumb pudding
directions: Use 2/3 crumbs in bottom of pan.
Mix margarine, sugar, eggs and pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put over crumb layer. Refrigerate for 12 hours, then sprinkle with rest of crumbs.

title: brandy apple crisp(special diet)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in an 8-inch square baking pan. Toss well; set aside.
Combine oats and brown sugar and flour in a small bowl.
Cut in margarine until well blended.
Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings; 1/2 cup per serving.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain grease; mix meat, Ragu, mushrooms, and cheese (grated or cubed).
Place in a rectangular baking dish. Pour cornbread batter over hamburger mixture.

title: chocolate-caramel-nut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon half of batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(Cake will
not test done.)
Cool cake for 10 minutes.

title: chipa guazu
directions: Grind corn, onion and cheese together in meat grinder.
In a large bowl, cream shortening.
Add eggs and salt, then corn mixture and milk.
Bake in greased square baking dish at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water for 45 minutes, then tear in pieces.
Mix soup, sour cream, chicken and mushrooms in casserole dish.
In separate bowl, add butter and water to moisten the dressing.
Sprinkle dressing over casserole ingredients.
Bake one hour at 350° (20 minutes in microwave).

title: gramma's cranberry cake
directions: Place cranberries, walnuts and sugar in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix and pour the remaining ingredients over cranberry mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: corn scallop
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Bake in a greased dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese on top; melt.
Serve.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken with salt in 3 or 4 quarts water until done (about 1 hour).
Bone chicken and let broth cool enough until fat comes to top, then skim off.
Add boned chicken, broth, carrots, onion and celery.
Cook until tender, then add egg noodles and let simmer for few minutes.
Do not overcook noodles.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Dip tomatoes in flour and fry or dip in Shake 'n Bake and put in oven until done.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine.
Coat chicken with flour and cook chicken in skillet over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Set chicken aside.

title: peanut and chocolate pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking pan or cookie sheet. Place pizza crust on pan.
Brush dough with vegetable oil.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes until puffed and lightly browned.
Place on wire racks.

title: foil cooked onion rings
directions: Mix all together, wrap in foil, grill for 30 minutes on grill or bake in oven for 30 minutes at 375.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
After loaf is formed, place strips of bacon on top of loaf.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, pineapple and pecans; mix well.
Layer vanilla wafers; spread 1/2 of mix over vanilla wafers. Add rest of mix.
Top with vanilla wafers.
Fix the day before serving.
Top with whipped cream or topping.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Cook, drain and crumble sausage.
Cool completely and mix with other ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Can be frozen and reheated at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: potato pancake appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Wrap potatoes in several layers of paper towels; squeeze to remove excess moisture. Beat egg, flour, salt and pepper in large bowl. Add potatoes, carrot and zucchini; mix well. Oil 2 nonstick baking sheets. Place vegetable mixture by heaping spoonfuls onto baking sheets; flatten slightly. Bake 8 to 15 minutes, until bottoms are browned. Turn; bake 5 to 10 minutes more. Stir together sour cream and herbs; serve with warm potatoes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry, orange and sugar together.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Mix plain gelatin with cold water.
Dissolve this with lemon Jell-O and hot water.
Let it cool a little, then add juice. When Jell-O mix begins to congeal, add celery, pecans and the cranberry mix.
Let salad finish congealing.

title: "hot jezebel"
directions: Mix preserves and seasonings together.
Can store for months in a tightly covered jar in the refrigerator.
To serve, slice cream cheese into thick slices and place in attractive bowl (slightly separated or fanned).
Pour over the cheese about 1/2 cup of the mix.
Serve with crackers and a "spreader" knife.
(Cream cheese is too thick to use crackers as a scoop.)

title: jam cake
directions: Mix
cocoa, sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream in butter; add beaten egg yolks, milk, flour and soda.
Add nuts, jam and raisins that have been soaked in hot water and finally fold in beaten egg whites.	Pour in a greased and floured tube pan and bake
for
1 hour or until tester comes out clean when inserted. Bake at 350°.

title: hazel walker's cranberry tea
directions: Cook cranberries and 1 quart water until they pop and are soft.
Strain (not push) and set aside.
In pan, put 2 cups water, red hots and cloves in bag.
Cook until red hots dissolve.
Add sugar and heat until dissolved. Pour in cranberry, orange and lemon juice, strain if you would like.
Add 2 quarts of water. Heat and serve.

title: tasty cheese ball
directions: Mix the cream cheese, Cheddar cold pack and butter together until blended.
Add the chopped onion, green pepper (if desired), Worcestershire sauce and chopped dried beef.
Mix well; refrigerate 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Shape into one ball or two and roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in Handi-Wrap, then foil.
Chill. May be made several days ahead of serving.
Good with crackers.
tags: Cheddar cold pack smoky cheese food

title: chicken dijon
directions: Wash and pat chicken dry.
Sprinkle with salt.
Combine sour cream and mustard.
Dip chicken breasts in mixture to coat, both sides, then dredge in seasoned bread crumbs mixed with Parmesan cheese and garlic salt.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and continue baking 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of large baking dish.
Roll chicken in melted butter; place on rice.
Mix chicken soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: chili cheese quiche
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish in microwave or oven.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add nuts. Sift dry ingredients and add to the first.
Shape into roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and let stand overnight.
Cut into slices and bake in moderate oven.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: In large 10 x 13-inch or 9 x 12-inch pan, spread 1/2 crushed cookies in bottom.
Beat softened ice cream.
Fold in Cool Whip and rest of cookies.
Freeze; thaw 5 minutes.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Place chicken on uncooked rice.
Use one cup in bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on chicken.
Mix together the soups with 1 cup of water or a little more.
Pour over chicken in pan.
Cook, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at around 375°.
I place foil over it and the last 15 minutes of baking, uncover.

title: old fashioned corn meal pancakes
directions: Mix well, but allow bubbles to remain in batter.
Grease griddle and make pancakes as large as you desire.
Don't try to fry pancakes too fast.
If batter is too heavy, add a little more buttermilk.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and garlic; drain.
Mix soup, sauce, milk and meat; stir well.
Line bottom of casserole dish with tortillas and place around side of dish.
Pour half of mixture on tortillas and sprinkle with half of cheese.
Pour rest of meat mixture and top with remainder of cheese.
Bake until hot and bubbly at 350°.

title: bill's quick-baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Microwave potatoes on High power for 4 to 6 minutes or until nearly done. If you wish, paint potatoes with oil and sprinkle with coarse salt. Place on middle oven rack with foil or baking sheet on lower. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, depending on size of potatoes. Yield: 4 servings.

title: cavatina
directions: Brown hamburger.
Saute onions and peppers.
Cook pasta.
Mix hamburger, onions, peppers and pasta together.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Add pepperoni and cheese.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: coconut cream pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: I usually don't measure my milk.
If you think it needs a little more, add some.
I usually double this when I make it.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Blend Ricotta and cream cheese.
Blend in sugar.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, cornstarch, flour and butter.
Fold in sour cream and blend well.

title: creole grillades with gravy (new orleans)
directions: Cut beef in 3-4 inch squares. Season with salt, pepper, cayenne. Heat lard in skillet. Add onion and garlic, saute. Stir in flour and brown.
Add tomatoes; cook two minutes. Add meat, brown on both sides. Combine vinegar and water and pour over meat. Simmer over low heat until done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together well bake till done at 350.

title: sausage and asparagus dinner
directions: Remove casings from sausage.
Cut into bite size pieces. Saute until browned.
Drain fat.
Clean and cut asparagus into pieces.
Pare and slice potatoes 1/4-inch.
Add asparagus, potatoes, onion and tomatoes to sausage.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not stir during cooking time.
Sprinkle croutons over vegetables; cover and heat 5 minutes more.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cut flowerets from broccoli; peel the stems and dice.
Combine broccoli flowerets, stems, onion, water, bouillon and garlic. Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Cool slightly.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well and baste last 1/2 hour.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar and salt. Cook until meat is done and most liquid has cooked out. Cook egg noodles until tender. Cream sour cream and cream cheese. Add onions and fold into the drained egg noodles. Layer meat, noodles and cheese in a large casserole dish. Bake in a 400° oven until cheese melts.

title: wet burritos
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain. Prepare taco seasoning mix as to package directions. Add to ground beef. Add refried beans to meat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes on medium to low heat. Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with cooking spray. Put ground beef mixture on tortilla. Add olives and onions. Roll up and place in baking dish. Pour enchilada sauce over burritos. Top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve with sour cream, salad, tortilla chips and salsa.

title: cheesy oven-fried chicken
directions: Coarsely
crush
dried
bread.
Combine
crushed
bread, Parmesan
cheese,
salt, onion powder, thyme, garlic powder and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in melted margarine or butter; roll in cheese mixture to coat.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up and not touching, in greased large shallow baking pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Do not turn.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown meat with 1/2 onion and the garlic powder; drain.
Saute green onions separately.
Julienne all vegetables and saute just until soft.
Drain on paper towels (can steam vegetables to avoid fat).
Mix all together.
Put in wrappers and moisten edges to seal.
Deep fry until brown.
Freezes well.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add stuffing mix and all other ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet in walnut size balls.
Freeze.
Transfer to plastic bag when frozen and return to freezer.
Bake as needed at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: homemade kahlua(adults only)
directions: Boil water.
Add sugar, coffee and rum.
Pour in 1/2 gallon jug and add vanilla bean.
Put in cool, dark place (basement) for 6 weeks.
Shake once a week or so.
Serve with half and half in tiny glass for an after dinner drink.

title: rhubarb mandarin crisp
directions: In a bowl, toss rhubarb, sugar and tapioca;
let stand for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Top with the oranges.
In a bowl, combine brown sugar, oats, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs, sprinkle evenly over oranges.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serve with ice cream if desired.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixing bowl, whisk together milk, buttermilk, egg, oil,
sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add corn meal and flour; mix well.
Blend in red peppers, jalapenos and corn.
Place in greased pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini apple pie
directions: Bring
zucchini,
apple
juice, lemon juice, spices and margarine to
a
boil; boil for 3 minutes.	Add cornstarch and water, stirring
constantly.
Cook	1 minute more; remove from heat.
Place
in
uncooked	pie shell; add top crust.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread and sliced bread finely.

Add sage, onion, celery, salt and pepper. Mix well, then add eggs and broth with bouillon dissolved to crumb mixture. Use enough broth to thoroughly moisten to cake batter mixture. Pour into crock-pot and cook on high for 4 to 6 hours.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in saucepan.
Add liquids; stir.
Cooking over medium heat, stir constantly until stiff (less than 5 minutes).

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix and vanilla pudding mix (mix dry).
Add oil and water.
Add one egg at a time, beating mixture after each egg addition.
Grease and flour an angel food cake pan and put in mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add flour, salt, sugar, 1/4 cup Crisco and remainder of water.
Add flour, if needed and work dough until it isn't sticky.
Grease top of dough.
Cover and let double in size (about 2 1/2 hours).
Pinch off dough and roll into biscuits (about the size of a small peach).
Flip biscuits over in a greased baking pan (remaining 1/4 cup Crisco goes in pan for baking).
Let rise until doubled again.
Bake at 350° until starts browning, then turn oven to 400° and bake until golden brown.

title: 2 step chicken broccoli divan
directions: In a 9-inch casserole dish, arrange broccoli.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: wanda's company casserole
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add spaghetti.
Cover and turn off heat. Let stand for 20 minutes.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Cream together margarine and the 1/2 cup sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla and flour, mixing well. Spread evenly in buttered 9-inch round cake pan.
Place apple wedges into cake batter to form a circular pattern.
Mix together 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cake.
Sprinkle top with almonds.

title: bobka
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk to beaten egg.
Stir into flour.
Wrap and chill.
Divide dough in half and roll.
Divide the meat mixture and spread on each piece of dough like a jelly roll.
Place on a greased pan and bake at 375° about 25 minutes. Slice to serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine in bowl with other ingredients.
Mix together and return to pan. Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour soups over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top.
Add cooking sherry and small amount water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put thawed chicken in large pot of water and let boil until chicken is done, or until chicken falls off the bones. Place 1/2 stick of butter and the bouillon cubes in the pot with chicken and let it all cook together.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in an airtight container. Makes about 3 cups mix.
To serve:
Spoon 2 tablespoons mix into a cup.
Add 1 cup hot milk and 2 tablespoons rum (if desired).
Stir until well mixed.
Garnish with a dollop of whipped cream and a cinnamon stick.

title: baked beans
directions: In casserole dish, add pork and beans and first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese until smooth and blend with eggs, 2/3 cup sugar and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in a moderately hot oven at 370° for 20 minutes.
Remove pie from oven; cool 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine sour cream with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Carefully spread over filling.
Return pie to very hot oven at 425° and bake 10 minutes.
Cool pie, then let sit overnight before serving.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O, water and pineapple.
Store in refrigerator until soft set.
Fold in chopped nuts and Cool Whip. Pour into mold.
Let set to firm and serve.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and celery.
Drain off fat.
Add rice, soy sauce, mushroom soup, chicken rice soup, water and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Place all ingredients in a casserole dish and mix well.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apricot spread
directions: Mix and serve with pumpkin bread.

title: can't fail pie crust
directions: Mix right in pie pan flour, sugar and salt.
Add oil and milk. Mix with mixture only until blended.
Pat dough evenly up sides and bottom of pie pan.
Make ridges on top.
Prick with fork if you are making a single crust.
Bake at 370° for 20 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Bake crust until done. Cool. Line bottom of crust with bananas. Mix sugar, milk and cornstarch. Cook in double boiler until thick. In another bowl, beat egg yolks and add small amount of cooked mixture to yolks. Beat until smooth. Add yolk mixture to remaining cooked mixture. Cook about 2 more minutes. Remove from heat and add butter flavoring, vanilla, salt and butter. Let cool. Pour over bananas and top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Set aside egg whites.
Cook in boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and spread on pie.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: missouri depression fruit cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water.
When tender, drain.
Mix together with lard or vegetable oil, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, cocoa, flour, soda and 1 cup cold water or fruit juice.
Add nuts and candied fruit.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 4 (3 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch) loaves. When cool, wrap in foil.
Store in refrigerator or freeze.

title: butter pecan cheesecake
directions: Combine first four ingredients, mixing well.
Reserve 1/3 cup mixture; firmly press remaining mixture on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy; gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each.
Add sour cream and flavorings; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan; sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes; reduce to 300° and bake 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Chill.

title: baked stuffed rabbit with carrots
directions: For stuffing, mash potatoes to make 2 cups.
Season with butter, salt, pepper, savory and celery.
Fill body of rabbit with this stuffing and sew it up.
Place quartered carrots beside it.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add flour; blend.
Add beet liquid; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and cloves; stir until sugar dissolves. Drain beets.
Add.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and egg. Pat into 10 x 7 rectangle. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet. Smooth with rolling pin. Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Put the chocolate bar on top of the pastry and cover with aluminum foil. When melted, spread chocolate. Cool. Cut into bars.

title: ground beef - green bean casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onions until browned.
In large casserole, mix the green beans, tomato soup and sauteed meat.

title: rich creamy fudge
directions: Coat a 13 x 9 pan with butter. In a large heavy saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk and butter. Heat over high heat until butter is melted and mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to medium; boil 6 minutes, until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla. Pour into buttered pan. Refrigerate until firm. Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Mix preceding ingredients (except cherry tomatoes).
Cut large cherry tomatoes in half and/or cut bottoms off small cherry tomatoes.
Drain cherry tomatoes upside down on paper towels. When cherry tomatoes are gutted and drained, fill with preceding mixture.

title: bananas supreme* * * * *
directions: It is unbelievable how easy this barbecue recipe is.
It was given to me by a friend from South Carolina back in the 50's.
The pepper rings are from a cookbook my youngest son gave me for Christmas one year.
It is so pretty and if you are entertaining at Christmas time, it makes a festive looking salad with the Christmas colors.
You could also serve the rings with an Italian meal, because the colors are the same as the Italian flag.

title: roast chicken stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients together until bread has absorbed all the egg.
Lightly salt and pepper chicken cavity and add stuffing.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make up the day before.
Serve on Triscuits.

title: sunny italy salad dressing
directions: Mix the warm water with sugar, then add the rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in greased casserole dish.
Melt cream cheese, butter and celery soup together.
Pour over potatoes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook uncovered for 45 minutes.
Cover and cook for 15 additional minutes.

title: autumn fruit salad
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and flour. Stir in water.
Bring to a boil. Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter and vanilla. Cool to room temperature.
In a large bowl, combine apples, grapes, celery and walnuts. Add the dressing and toss.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In a saucepan combine butter, cocoa, sugar and milk. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat; add quick oats and peanut butter, mix well. Add softened butter. Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Cool and they are ready to eat.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Sprinkle both sides of the brisket liberally with the following:
liquid smoke, celery salt, nutmeg, paprika, garlic salt and meat tenderizer.
Wrap in heavy-duty foil and leave in the refrigerator for 8 hours, preferably overnight.
Cook in foil in large, shallow pan for about 3 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool; drain juice, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Slice brisket and set aside.

title: slippery elms
directions: Peel and quarter ripe cucumbers.
Remove seeds and put in large pan with 1/2 cup salt.
Let set overnight.
Drain and pour hot water over them and drain again.
Cook until tender in following mixture:
brown sugar, white sugar, vinegar, hot water, mustard seed and turmeric.
Put in jars while hot.
Turn over to seal.

title: layered salad
directions: Combine top 5 ingredients in layers.
Cover with Swiss cheese. Cover top with mayonnaise, sealing the edges.
Let set for 24 hours.
Mix well when ready to serve.

title: orange balls(no baking required!)
directions: Mix cookie wafer crumbs, coconut and powdered sugar in a bowl. Add orange juice concentrate.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional powdered sugar.
Store in covered container overnight. If mixture is too soft, add a few more vanilla wafers (crushed).

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Beat in cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Drain broccoli and pat dry.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Spread with spoon.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until firm and pulls away from sides.

title: pasta with tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, basil, garlic, salt and pepper; set aside at room temperature for several hours.
Serve over hot pasta.
If desired, garnish with basil and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite size pieces.
Toss with dressing. Serves 8 to 10.

title: crunchy minglers snack mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Ranch dressing, and toss well. Heat in microwave on High for 1 minute.
Sprinkle dressing mix on top and toss again until well blended.
Makes 13 cups.

title: candied fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Butter loaf pans and line with brown paper. Bake at 375 degrees for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Brush corn syrup on cakes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except stuffing.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix butter, sugar, flour and pecans. Press evenly in bottom of ungreased 9 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake until light brown, about 12 minutes. Crumble with spoon and cool. Set aside 1 cup crumbs and press rest of crumbs in bottom of pan. Pack ice cream on top of crumbs. Sprinkle the reserved crumbs on top of ice cream. Wrap and freeze. Heat filling until hot. Cut ice cream in 3-inch squares. Spoon warm pie filling onto ice cream bars. Serve immediately.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until the size of small peas.
Add water, a little at a time.
Gather dough into a ball. Cut into 12 parts.
Roll into balls; brush with shortening. Cover; let rest a few minutes.
Roll into circles; cook on dry, hot griddle or skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook about 2 minutes and turn.
Cook an additional minute.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and let stand for 3 to 5 minutes.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 425°.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until done.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Cook spaghetti (3 cups); stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Place spaghetti as crust in pie pan or casserole dish.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti. Spread ground beef over cottage cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°. Then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: veg-all chestnut casserole
directions: Mix
Veg-All, cheese, onion, mayonnaise and water chestnuts. Put
in casserole dish and cover with cracker crumbs and margarine.	Bake
in
a
oven
for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly and crumbs are lightly browned.

title: dutch oven meat loaf
directions: Mix all but
last
ingredients
in a bowl.
Put in a 2-quart Dutch
oven
or
meat loaf pan.
Top with bacon strips and squeeze a little more catsup on top.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Drain excess fat; serve.

title: cinnamon red hot cucumber pickles
directions: Peel, seed and slice cucumbers.
Soak in lime and 1 gallon water for 24 hours.
Wash; soak covered with ice water for 3 hours.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, red food coloring, alum and water to cover.
Pour over cucumbers and simmer 2 hours; pour off water. Bring 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, sugar, cinnamon sticks and red hots to boil.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours; pour off and boil.
Pour over cucumbers in jars and seal.
These cucumbers taste like cinnamon apple rings.

title: sandy's homemade bread
directions: Put salt, sugar, shortening and water in large mixing bowl. Add warm water and stir.
Sprinkle yeast over water and let set for 5 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add 2 cups of flour and beat thoroughly.
Add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
When unable to mix well with a spoon, mix with your hands.
Mix until dough begins to get stiff and hard to mix in flour.
Pour dough onto a well-floured surface; sprinkle with flour on top.
Let dough rest for 5 minutes while you wash your bowl.
Knead dough 5 to 10 minutes; sprinkle with flour as necessary until dough is smooth, elastic and no longer sticky.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly first 5 ingredients.
Blend in the remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls. Use fork dipped in flour for crisscross pattern.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 9 dozen.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon in baking dish.
Cover top with bacon strips.
Bake until bubbly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until soft.
Salt and pepper.
Drain squash.
In mixing bowl add squash, butter, cheese, egg and half of broken crackers.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Heat juice and pudding, stirring constantly until thick. Cool.
Add the fruit.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain juice.
Should be 1 cup, if not, add water.
Bring to boil and add jello.
Stir until dissolved, then add 2 cups of cold water.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Let congeal.

title: easy cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cheese until it's light and fluffy. Add condensed milk, vanilla
and
lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Let chill
until
mixture gets firm.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Any fruit can be used as topping.

title: good red kool-aid punch
directions: Mix in a 1-gallon jug. Fill with water. At serving time, add 1 quart ginger ale per gallon to punch bowl.

title: tijuana pie
directions: Brown meat and season to taste.
Drain.
While meat is cooking, mix all cans and heat through.
Grease crock pot with non-stick cooking spray.
Layer chips, meat, sauce and cheese, until all is used.
Heat in crock pot until cheese is melted.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: Add the cornstarch and sugar to the water. Heat until mixture boils and turns clear. Beat egg whites to a peak. Add cornstarch mixture to the egg whites. Add 7 teaspoons sugar to this and beat until whites are stiff.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, condensed milk and lime juice.
Pour into pastry shell.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and chill 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.
Slice lime into thin slices and garnish pie.
Refrigerate.

title: fudge scotch squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together until crumbs are moist.
Spread into greased 8 x 8-inch glass pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fairy food(angel food candy)
directions: Butter 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
First measure out baking soda. Combine sugar, syrup and vinegar in heavy saucepan.
Continue to cook without stirring to 300° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in baking soda, mixing well.
Pour in buttered pan.
It will spread itself.
Cool.
Break into pieces. Dip in melted chocolate and put on waxed paper to harden.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: peach supreme
directions: Mix together the egg yolks, macaroons, oleo and sugar.
Put peach halves in shallow baking pan.
Put a large tablespoon of macaroon filling in each peach.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: chicken pods
directions: Use a 9 x 9-inch deep pan.

title: rosemary jalapeno roasted chicken breast with grilled vegetables
directions: Remove skin and wing bones from chicken; season.
Squeeze lime juice on chicken and sprinkle with jalapeno and rosemary.
Set aside for 2 hours.
Thickly slice zucchini and tomato (1/4-inch thick).
Blanch scallions for 5 seconds.
Brush vegetables with olive oil.
Season and grill until well marked.
Chill and dice. Add sour cream and cilantro.
Gently pound chicken and roll up, slightly overwrapping the edges.
Place chicken, loin side down, on a roasting sheet.
Brush with oil and roast until done, approximately 20 minutes, at 350°.
Chill and serve.

title: pink punch
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, juice and sugar.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Remove cartilage from crabmeat.
Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Stir until smooth.
Slowly stir in chicken broth and pepper.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add half and half slowly, and then the milk, slowly.
Stir constantly until thick.
Do not let it boil.
Add crabmeat and salt.
Sprinkle Old Bay seasoning over soup after it has been put in bowl.
Serve hot.

title: orange salad 2
directions: Drain oranges. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl. Refrigerate.
Use dry jello.

title: blueberry crescent pastries
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles. Divide cream cheese in to 8 equal pieces. Spread 1 piece on square corner of each triangle, about 1/4-inch from edge.
Top with 1 teaspoon preserves.
Fold 2 remaining points to square corner, making
square shaped pocket.
Press edges to seal. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Brush with margarine. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over pastries.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes at 375° until golden brown.
Makes 8 pastries.

title: green grape salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill and serve.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet cook sausage until brown.
Drain off excess fat. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with point toward center.
Press over bottom and sides to form a crust.
Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredient together with a spoon. (DO NOT USE MIXER.) Bake in greased and floured pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach souffle and baked eggs
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spoon spinach into 2 ramekins.
Make indentations and break eggs into cups.
Bake 20 minutes until spinach is hot and puffed and eggs are done.
Sprinkle cheese and paprika over mixture.

title: oven fried green tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper in a bowl and set aside.
Beat egg and water together in another bowl. Dip tomato slices first in egg and then dredge in cornmeal.
Place tomato layers in baking dish using only enough vegetable cooking spray to keep tomatoes from sticking.
Bake 20 minutes and turn with spatula and bake 20 more minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cook slowly in an iron skillet at 350° for about 15 minutes, or until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Cool slightly.
Shape into balls with buttered hands.
Roll in coconut. Keep in a cool place.
Yield:
50 balls.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Set aside to cool.
When it is fully cooled, add grated cheese, kidney beans and tomatoes.
Add just before serving the crushed nacho chips and salad dressing. That way it won't get soggy.
Mix well.

title: almond toffee triangles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt. Spread dough in pan.
Bake until light golden brown, 18 to 20 minutes.
Prepare topping.

title: eggrolls
directions: Brown meat in oil and set aside.
Saute garlic until golden brown; add onion.
Cook until done, add meat, then carrots. Continue stirring until half done, add green beans.
Cook until half done; add cabbage, celery and water chestnuts.
Season with salt, soy sauce and pepper to taste.
Cook until half done.
Remove from heat and put in strainer to drain.
Let cool.
Put filling in wrappers following instructions on package.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and heat to boiling; remove garlic.
Dip meats in sauce before broiling or roasting or use to baste during roasting.
Approximate yield:
2 cups sauce.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine 1/4 can of the mushroom soup with all the ingredients except the water and the mushroom gravy.
Shape into patties. Arrange in shallow pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining mushroom soup and water.
Pour this and the mushroom gravy over the patties and bake another 10 minutes.

title: inside out cabbage rolls
directions: Saute cabbage and onion in skillet with pam. When tender, combine remaining ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake
at 350 for 20 minutes.

title: easy no-roll pie crust
directions: Place all ingredients in pie pan and mix with a fork.
Press dough in pan and along sides.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until light brown.
Makes 1 crust.

title: "cincinnati famous chili recipe"
directions: Brown meat; cook onions with meat and drain grease.
Place meat and onions in large pan or crock-pot.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook slowly 4 to 5 hours, covered.
Remove bay leaves and garlic before serving.
Serve on a bed of spaghetti and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: piquant pickles
directions: Drain pickles and put slices in large bowl.
Add all ingredients to pickles and stir occasionally.
After sugar dissolves, put back in jar or in pint jars.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Bake according to directions on cake mix box.
Cool and ice.

title: fried cheese
directions: Cut cheese into 2 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Dip each in flour, then beaten egg, then bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil for 1 minute, turn and fry 1 more minute or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with pizza sauce, if desired.

title: alabama pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture, a cup at a time.
Alternate with milk.
Add flavoring. Pour in prepared tube pan and bake at 325° for one hour in floured and greased pan.

title: chicken in spicy cream sauce
directions: Mix garlic, paprika and salt in bowl.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Rub with garlic mixture; let stand for 15 minutes.
Cook in hot oil in large skillet for 7 to 8 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Spoon mixture of half and half and lemon juice over chicken.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until tender, turning once.
Place chicken on warm serving dish.
Spoon sauce over top; garnish with parsley.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: date ball
directions: Place everything in pan over medium heat except Rice Krispies and nuts.
Cook 6 minutes; remove and add nuts and Krispies.
Roll in ball and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce; stir well.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mee mee's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs on low speed.
Mix all other ingredients together. Put in unbaked pie shell and dot with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
After it has browned as much as you want then cover with foil.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Chill
dough 3 to 4 hours.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook beans as directed on package. In skillet, saute onions and bell pepper in cooking oil for about 1 minute.
Add hamburger and brown, stirring often. Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and chili pepper. Salt to taste and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add all to beans. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer for about 1 hour.
For smaller amount, use half recipe.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over the oatmeal.
Set aside and cool.
Combine the white sugar, brown sugar and oil.
Add the eggs and cream together.
Add the flour, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and salt. Add the oatmeal mixture. Beat 3 minutes and bake in oblong pan for 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and frost.

title: cucumber dill pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets.
Cover with vinegar; add cloves, sugar and lemon. Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Separate onions into rings; add to beets.
Chill until serving time.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Combine bread crumbs, milk, meat, onion, salt and pepper. Form into patties with your burger press.
Combine Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, sugar and catsup.
Brown the burgers on both sides in the hot bacon fat; add the sauce.
Cover and cook 10 minutes. Makes 8 hamburgers.

title: deer path salad
directions: Drain juice from 1 large can crushed pineapple, save 1/4 cup liquid.
Add 1/4 cup juice to 1 envelope of unflavored gelatin. Add 1/2 cup of sugar to pineapple.
Stir and boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add gelatin mixture.
Break 8 ounces cream cheese into mixture.
Stir until cream cheese is nearly melted. Add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Mix well and pour into mold or square pan. Set until firm.
Can be made 2 to 3 days ahead.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins or fruit cocktail in water until the water is gone.
Then add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and cooking oil.
Mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: cathy's beef burgundy
directions: Cut beef into bite size pieces and brown in oil. Add onions and flour; stir to coat meat. Add wine, broth and seasonings. Cover and simmer for 90 minutes. Remove bay leaf and add mushrooms and simmer for 5 minutes. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line a greased pizza pan with the crescent rolls.
Bake until golden brown.
Allow to cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and Ranch dressing together until smooth.
Spread onto the cooled crescent rolls.
Add the broccoli, cauliflower, carrots and ripe olives. Refrigerate for 1 hour and slice and serve.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, margarine and salt in medium saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly over moderate heat.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate morsels and stir until melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm. Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: taco chicken
directions: Place chips in casserole. Put chicken on top. Mix soup, tomatoes and water or broth together. Pour over chips and chicken. Heat until boiling hot.

title: flossie's yeast bread
directions: Mix and pour out on floured cloth.
Knead 10 minutes.
Put in warm place to rise until double in bulk.
Punch down, cover and let rest a few minutes.
Divide.
Roll out into oblong rolls about 18 inches.
Roll up and put in greased loaf pan.
Put seam in batter.
Makes 2 loaves.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° until brown.
May have to put foil over top to keep it from browning too much.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts.
Chill until slightly firm.
Form into desired shape.
Garnish with nuts. Chill several hours.
(All "light" products may be substituted.)

title: hamburger stuffed bread
directions: Cut top of French bread. Hollow out bottom of loaf. Leave approximately 1/2 inch on sides and bottom. Tear the bread, which was hollowed out, into 1 inch pieces; set aside.

title: lemon-poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix together. Pour 1/2 full into 5 baby loaf pans (5 3/4 x 3 1/4 x 2 inch). Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes. Remove from oven and pierce holes in top of loaves using toothpick. Just before loaves are removed from oven, cook glaze.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well. Sift together dry ingredients and combine mixtures.
Stir until dough is stiff.
Shape into balls and press with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: clam stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and saute chopped stems in butter for 10 minutes.
Add minced clams, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic powder and saute 5 minutes.
Stuff caps; place in greased baking dish and chill.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard and top each cap. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: In a large bowl, sift together the flour and onion salt; mix in basil.
Cut in butter and lard until it resembles coarse meal. Gradually add enough water to hold dough together, mixing lightly with a fork.
Roll out on lightly floured board.
Line 9-inch pie plate with dough.

title: pumpkin pies (2)
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into unbaked pie crusts. Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes, then in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite sized pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and cook over kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 450°.
This will serve 3,800 people. If more are expected, then add 2 rabbits.
But do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: oatmeal crispies cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well and add flour, soda, nuts and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Chill and drop by teaspoons.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: potato cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl, except oil.
Mix well.
Drain any liquid that accumulates.
Pour oil in skillet to 1/8 inch deep.
Heat to 350°.
Drop potato mixture, 1/4 c. at time, into hot oil.
Flatten, forming a circle.
Cook 3 minutes on each side or until potatoes are brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: wassail(english holiday drink)
directions: In 3-quart casserole, place cider, allspice, cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon sticks, orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and apples. Microwave on High (10) for 15 to 18 minutes, until hot.
Strain and serve.

title: corned beef and asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus and corned beef in layers in casserole dish. Mix together butter, milk and flour and cook to make a white sauce. Mix Creamettes and soup and pour over casserole contents. Add the white sauce and sprinkle with 1/4 pound grated Alberta cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ranch house steak
directions: Cut meat in serving size pieces; trim excess fat.
Slash edges of meat to prevent curling.
Combine flour, mustard, salt and pepper; coat meat with mixture.
(Set aside any remaining flour mixture.)
In heavy skillet, brown meat on both sides in hot oil. Add reserved flour mixture to skillet.
Combine water and Worcestershire.
Stir into mixture in skillet.
Cover lightly; cook over low heat for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat.
Skim excess fat from pan juices.
Drizzle juices over meat.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Note:
Need 8-inch diameter plastic flower pot.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix in order given.
May be baked immediately or pinched off as needed.
Keep in refrigerator.
Bake at 450°.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together.
Pour into a hot greased pan and bake at 350° until bread is brown.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Add egg, milk and corn.
Stir until blended.
Drop in hot oil, a teaspoonful at a time.
Brown. Remove and drain. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve hot.
They look like little oblong doughnuts when finished.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/2 cup of the liquid.
Combine all ingredients except beets.
Bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove cinnamon stick and add beets.
Let cool some and put in airtight container, jar with lid.
Store in refrigerator, mixing occasionally, for 1 week.
Serve cold.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs, sugar, margarine, pudding mix, vanilla flavoring, ginger and milk in a large mixer bowl until well blended.
Pour into shells and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of a double boiler; cool to room temperature.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar until creamy.
Add chocolate mixture to eggs, beating by hand.
Add salt, flour, nuts and vanilla; blend well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 20.

title: humdingers
directions: Cook chopped dates, melted butter and sugar.
Cook on low until mixture comes to a boil, about 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Let cool.
Make into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: banana cake delight
directions: Mix all together thoroughly. Pour into a tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: better than fried chicken
directions: In a large bowl, combine first eight ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinade; coat each piece with crumbs.
Arrange on a shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until juices run clear. Yield:
8 servings.
Diabetic Exchanges:
One serving equals 3 1/2 lean meat, 1 starch, 1/4 skim milk; also, 271 calories, 293 mg sodium, 76 mg cholesterol, 22 gm carbohydrate, 32 gm protein and 5 gm fat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fry onion in butter.
Stir in flour; add water and cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Blend in cheese and add broccoli.
Mix in eggs until gently blended.
Use 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with crackers and dot with butter before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jayme's tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed.
Stir in soup and milk.
Gently fold in tuna and peas.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: rum cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate decadent pie
directions: To Make Crust: In food processor, crush chocolate wafers and add butter.
Press into 9-inch pie plate and freeze for 1 hour.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix and put in a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Cut or mark out 20 squares.
Place 1 heaping tablespoon of pie filling on each square.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch or a bit larger jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: "el toro" cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese into a crock-pot.
Add water and remaining ingredients.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Boil noodles, then drain.
Brown meat, then drain.
Add sauce. Pour into pan.
Add cheese.
Bake until cheese melts and browns. Let sit about 10 minutes, then serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Set oven to 425°.
Cream shortening and the brown and white sugars. Add pineapple and egg to the cream mixture.
Add the dry ingredients: flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda to mixture. Add vanilla and walnuts to
mixture.
Drop by level teaspoon on greased or sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat cook beef until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Meanwhile cut each biscuit into quarters. Remove dish from oven and stir.
Arrange biscuits around hot beef mixture. Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: slaw (tart!)
directions: Shred cabbage.
Place in a plastic container a layer of cabbage, then a layer of shredded onions and chopped pepper until all used up.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard and celery seed.
Heat to a boil.
Spoon hot mixture over cabbage.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Will last for a week or more.

title: marinated cheese
directions: Combine ingredients in a small jar; cover tightly, and shake vigorously to blend.
Set aside.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Mix. Grease 8-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tasty turkey pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix dressing, flour, bouillon and pepper in saucepan; gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring frequently, over medium-low heat until thickened.
Add turkey and vegetables. Cook, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly heated.
Spoon into 8-inch square baking dish.
Unroll dough in 2 rectangles.
Press perforations together to seal.
Place rectangles side by side to form square; press edges together to form seam.
Cut dough into 1-inch strips.
Arrange in lattice design over turkey mixture. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: strawberry flumery
directions: Combine in a saucepan, 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk (a wire whisk works great).
Cook and stir until it boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir about a cup of warmed ingredients into the egg yolk in a separate bowl.
Add this mixture back into saucepan with the hot mixture.
Return to stove and cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and pour into a dish.
Chill.
Serve with strawberries on top.

title: cranberry salad
